text:
part 5
third parties such as judges, police officers, and juries often justify the perpetrator's actions and accuse the victim of the crime. they draw attention to objectifying a person sexually, which can alter the way a person is viewed.  objectifying a person can lead the victim to be seen as a “lesser victim” compared to a non-objectified person. that materializing and sexualizing a person can alter the whole case and how they end up criticizing the victim. for example, there was a trail in ireland where a seventeen-year-olds lace-front thong, was used as evidence of her consent in a rape case. the 27-year-old man was acquitted and the defense lawyer argued that that the teenager consented to sex because “you have to look at the way she was dressed.” this controversy led women to start sharing their lacy underwear on social media with the hashtag #thisisnotconsent condemning victim shaming. 
there are double standards in sexual activities when it comes to men and women. for example women who are sexually active tend to get bad reputations and are known as “sluts” however if a male does the exact same thing they receive a pat on the back for it. another component that explains how gender relations, and the treatment of women, and attitudes toward rape all underline on why women are being belittled and  ow rape culture has sadly become the new “norm.” especially when it comes to social media it can either have a positive effect like starting a movement such as the #metoomovement. or it can have a negative connotation such as the grounded theory called the “banner incident” that happened on freshman move-in day at southeastern university. the banners said: “rowdy and fun. hope your baby girl is ready for a good time;” “freshman daughter drop off;” and “go ahead and drop off mom too.” #rapeculture  #thisisnotconsent  #victimblaming  #victimawareness #metoo #whyididntreport #howiwillchange

text:
part 4
this is where your gender and drinking comes into play with rape myth acceptance. rape myth is defined as attitudes and false assumptions held about rape that rejects or diminish victims injury and blames the victim for their own victimization. males are almost encouraged by their peers to objectify women, due to their sexual aggression; that there is a double standard when it comes to men and women drinking. it is stated that forty-one percent believed that if a woman was raped while intoxicated then she was responsible for the incident. there are different sets of rules that women and men have been obeying by.  for example binge drinking in a college setting is often normalized and so is men being praised for it. while when it comes to women, they are expected to have a certain composure to them. rape culture makes you carry yourself a certain way it also affects the way you think of certain things. how certain clothes and the way you wear them can bring up the idea that you “were asking for it” and how you can never really let your guard down.
#rapeculture  #thisisnotconsent  #victimblaming  #victimawareness #metoo #whyididntreport #howiwillchange

text:
part 3
if they do decide to hold off on filing a report, it is more likely that they will not be believed. this is due to the fact that you would need to get a sexual assault forensic examination also known as a “rape kit” within the seventy-two hours of the occurrence. this examination helps preserve any evidence such as dna to be stored if you choose to report the incident. without that evidence, it would be hard to convict the perpetrator, and it would make it seem as if the victim lied about the occurrence. 
our society has taught us that women should take extra measures to secure our safety. there are these little things we do, that we don't even realize we are doing them until you question why you are doing it. from a young age, woman are taught to watch what they wear, to only go out in groups, to holding keys out as a potential weapon, and parking in well-lit areas never questioning why. while men are never taught that or give any of these things a second thought once they walk out their house. 
#rapeculture  #thisisnotconsent  #victimblaming  #victimawareness #metoo #whyididntreport #howiwillchange

december 06 | day 12

our society teaches women to avoid being raped when we should be teaching men not to rape. this encourages the rape culture that is seen. existing norms and practices need to be broken down by educating our young boys on positive masculinity so they don’t grow up to be perpetrators.

respecting physical boundaries, understanding consent and accepting the rights of women should be embraced by every young boy and man. 
let’s have these conversations with our boys, so they become protectors of women and not perpetrators.

text:
part 2
it is often referred to as victim blaming which is holding sexually assaulted victims responsible for their action, instead of holding the perpetrator accountable. people are more likely to blame the victim if they believe the victim could have stopped the perpetrator from raping them. if a woman does decide to report the incident they will likely be asked “were you drunk” or “what were you wearing.” that is why i chose this photo, it is a perfect example of how in rape culture these are the first questions that come to mind. while the hands in the photo portray, how society silences women when it comes to sexual assault. 
people tend to focus on what choice the victim made that lead to that incident, instead of focusing on the actual perpetrator. these questions can discourage a victim from speaking out, five out of six victims do not file a police report. in the article, why don't victims of sexual harassment come forward sooner? it states “ the equal employment opportunity commission reports receiving 12,000 allegations of sex-based harassment each year, with only accounting 83 percent “of the complaints.” why are the rest of the people staying silent? even though it is common for the victim to stay silent and delay discussing their incidents, the source psychology today, explains why women are sexually assaulted, blamed, and not having a choice in coming forward.
#rapeculture  #thisisnotconsent  #victimblaming  #victimawareness #metoo #whyididntreport #howiwillchange

text:
vaak ken je alleen de top van de ijsberg. het onbewuste zes zevende deel onder water ben je je niet bewust, en komt dus je bewustzijn niet binnen als informatie.  en dat kan je sabotteren. zoals mensen die een ernstig auto ongeluk riskeren. niet omdat ze opeens zulke slechte bestuurders zijn geworden, maar omdat ze sterke onbewuste schuldgevoelens hebben, bijvoorbeeld. jaren later komt men er achter dat ze zich schuldig voelen aan de dood van iemand. 
ook als je probeert lastige eigenschappen van jezelf te verbloemen, 'onder water te duwen', kan het zomaar als een strandbal die je lang onder water probeert te duwen in je gezicht terecht komen. 
ik moest daar aan denken bij die amerikaanse opperrechter, die voor zijn benoeming aangeklaagd werd wegens seksueel overschrijdend gedrag. een #metoo dus. en hij had al die jaren zo'n vroom, braaf leven geleid! het lijkt erop dat zijn wilde kant de 'strandbal' was die hij jarenlang onder water duwde.

kennen jullie dit soort voorbeelden? ben daar echt benieuwd naar!

text:
note to self: be careful what you ask for especially when asking questions of people that are far more brilliant than you could have ever imagined! my professor has me studying deep psychology, sexuality, philosophy, spirituality, feminist theory, and eroticism through the inquiry of gendered power dynamics! let’s couple that with the social de-construction of this reality simply because i asked: how can we shift out of hierarchical systems of power-over into collaborative power-with one another through the lens of gender and racial equality? is it possible to shift consciousness through media, action research, and/or performance as inquiry? i have been particularly interested in raising consciousness, the ascension of humanity, how to eradicate poverty, and how to create systems and social change. 
i know right! who thinks of these kinds of things?!?! apparently i do and then i get myself in way too deep! my life would be so much simpler if all i cared about was monday night football!!! that’s ok though. i know i’m not alone... the top 3 social issues americans talk the most about on twitter
1. better transportation and roads. ...
2. reliable energy at home. ...
3. equality between men and women. ... women’s equality and the #metoo movement are creating huge strides for women’s empowerment! these are all important questions of our time!

here is a sampling of only a few of the books and videos on my required reading list in case you fancy reading complex theory or feel inclined to watch educational videos. i have to say that reading the history of sexuality by michel foucault and the mermaid and the minotaur by dorothy dinnerstein are by far the most intellectually challenging! i welcome anyone’s input or other book recommendations. feel free to read and watch a sample of these and let me know your thoughts.... the videos can be found on youtube! i’m not going to lie, these books and videos will challenge your beliefs and perceptual awareness!  my recommendation is to be intellectually curious and open-minded!  i don’t know how i get myself into these deep intellectual spaces but here i am ... thanks for joining me on this journey!

here is a sampling of only a few of the books and videos on my required reading list in case you fancy reading complex theory or feel inclined to watch educational videos. i have to say that reading the history of sexuality by michel foucault and the mermaid and the minotaur by dorothy dinnerstein are by far the most intellectually challenging! i welcome anyone’s input or other book recommendations. feel free to read and watch a sample of these and let me know your thoughts.... the videos can be found on youtube! i’m not going to lie, these books and videos will challenge your beliefs and perceptual awareness!  my recommendation is to be intellectually curious and open-minded!  i don’t know how i get myself into these deep intellectual spaces but here i am ... thanks for joining me on this journey!

igår var jag hos min tillfälliga kurator. det var sista gången även om jag får ringa vid behov. jag har aldrig planerat innan vad som ska avhandlas innan utan har tagit det som det kommer. alla människor borde någon gång ta chansen att mötas fritt med en människa som står under tystnadsplikt. vi talade om en händelse jag var med om när jag var 19, i detalj. om hur jag inte blev backad eller ens trodd. om hur försoningen tillslut kom i samband med #metoo inte för att någon upprättelse någonsin kommer att komma egentligen men hur mina lika unga vänner som fanns runt mig då, tog emot mig nu. vi lyfta kvinnors styrka och modet att dela med sig av tunga saker. och vi gick igen igenom alla dimmiga dagar i samband med min sjukdom och det märkliga tillstånd när man nästan dör, men bara nästan. jag kunde inte sova i morse och gjorde då min hemläxa. som stavas vita arkivet. det kändes som en lättnad även om det också var lite jobbigt. men tänk så himla bra för ens anhöriga, och att göra det innan man blir gaggig och för gammal liksom! asbra grej om ni frågar mig. tack för ordet.
ha en allvarsam, glad, kärleksfull eller vad du behöver idag: fredag ❤️

text:
i’d be remise in this talk about #queerbodies on land if i didn’t talk about this body that i live in.  i’m nonbinary trans, and have grappled with my body and how it shows up in the wider world since i was a tiny human. 
this body is a complicated, able and yet dysfunctional body.  this body was hyper feminized for years, and as a result hyper sexualized in myriad of damaging ways.  this body suffered 29 years of undiagnosed autoimmune disorder.  this body has survived more physical assault and suffering than i want to list here, cause this is the internet and we’re just getting to know each other. 
this body also thrives on land, jumps at the chance to dig into farm chores, seeks ritual, practice and pattern and is deeply connected to intuition. 
this body collaborates with 100s of thousands of small insect bodies every year, and lots of human bodies too.  this body has a flow space out on this land— a big beautiful one that works in cycles responsive to the land and the seasons. 
the fact that this body can do the work i ask it to do every day is a privilege and a blessing.  it’s an incredible testament to sheer resilient queer magic that it’s here, and i do my best to thank it every day for showing up for me. 
being on this land in this body has helped me begin a steady transition into a more fully realized sense of self and thus a more true presentation in the wider world. 
this has been angela from @yardbirdsbees posting for @countryqueers

#nonbinarybabes #queerfarmers #queerfolk #countryqueers #nonbinarybeauty #chronicillness #hurtssogood #loveyourbody #metoo #fuckthebinary

another one! we’re getting into a groove here, folks. vito discovers that alan got the drive to learn how to read by playing pokemon, and suddenly alan shouting “rudy ortiz! i choose you!” makes so much sense. the great rudy ortiz joins us and gives his views on road rage, divulges his early beginnings as a rapper from san leandro, and lets us know what it was like working with carlos mencia. we also take a moment to reflect on the #metoo movement and where we go from here as a society in terms of whether we can forgive or whether we still want to see people hang from the gallows. all in all, a lighthearted romp.

text:
give the gift of "i am divinity" to all the women you love. 
order by dec 12 (u.s. only) to receive by christmas.
sizes 10"x6" up to 20"x12"
when commissioned to paint the silhouette of a woman’s body for a hotel project--i was amazed at what i created!  inspired to use red acrylics on red metal with a touch of gold representing the god within, painting “divinity” empowered me.  because like many women, i also relate to the #metoo movement.
“i am divinity” honors the true beauty of women. love, sensuality, spirituality, strength, passion, sense of humor, compassion, intelligence, power. . .  i deeply and completely love and value myself because i am divinity! "i am divinity" is stunning on my metal product. 
#metoo #iam #divinity #ilovemyself #ihonormyself #womenpower #goddess

kasus pelecahan merupakan kasus serius yang seringkali disepelehkan. banyak korban pelecehan yang memilih diam dan menutupi pelecehan yang terjadi pada dirinya karena takut. biasanya korban pelecehan malah akan diserang secara verbal, korban disalahkan karena cara berpakaiannya, atau karena attitude-nya. padahal dia adalah korban, ironis memang sudah jatuh tertimpa tangga. victim shamming seperti ini yang akhirnya membuat korban takut dan memilih untuk diam. sedangkan pelaku, kebanyakkan masih bebas dan melakukannya lagi terhadap korban lain.

budaya menyalahkan wanita yang berpakaian terlalu vulgar sepertinya sudah ketinggalan jaman, korban pelecehan bukan hanya wanita saja tetapi semua orang bisa dan bahkan pernah menjadi korban. pelecehan terjadi tidak semata-mata hanya kepada wanita melaikan terjadi juga kepada orang tua, anak kecil, penyandang disabilitas dan bahkan pria dewasa, semua orang bisa menjadi korban pelecehan. pelecehan seksual merupakan masalah mengakar yang akan sangat sulit untuk diberantas apalagi dengan diamnya korban, pelaku kejahatan seksual ini semakin bebas merajalela. sex education dan pelajaran moral etika sedari dini merupakan langkah preventif yang bisa dilakukan oleh pemerintah. perlindungan terhadap korban seperti memberikan pendampingan atas trauma dan perlindungan hukum kepada korban dan saksi, dan sanksi kepada pelaku merupakan langkah yang dapat dilakukan saat terjadi kasus pelecehan. -cont-
name: ｎ ｏ ｂ ｉ ａ

text:
#台灣 #導演兼 #演員 #鈕承澤 日前傳出拍攝由 #任賢齊 主演嘅電影《 #跑馬 》期間，涉嫌 #性侵 一名女工作人員。事發後鈕承澤未有現身，據台灣傳媒報道，他情況好差，試過向受害人求饒；又反鎖自己在家。最後他終於喺社交平台出 post ，話自己承受好大壓力，但一定會勇於面對，絕不逃避。
網民聯想力好豐富嘅，馬上就諗到鈕承澤喺自導自演嘅電影《愛love》入面，佢同舒淇嘅「床戲」會唔會都係「自肥」咁加上去？舒淇經理人無回應到，不過舒淇本人就用個人帳戶回複咗「勇敢面對」去鈕承澤嘅 post，算係出言支持導演？
.
.
.

text:
thursday after-work consisted of an intimate, safe space to hear from the eloquent and brave @ashley_judd. she discussed #metoo, #timesup, a bit of her legal case against harvey weinstein, family, self-care, and women supporting women. here are my takes always: * hw was recently quoted saying “i've had one hell of a year… the worst nightmare of my life. ...” hw is experiencing darvo. darvo refers to a reaction perpetrators of wrong doing, particularly sexual offenders, may display in response to being held accountable for their behavior. darvo stands for "deny, attack, and reverse victim and offender."
* forgiveness is your own favor.
* denial stands for don't even notice i am lying.
* when asked ‘who do you wanna be when you grow up?’ ashley judd responds, “myself, just more so!” this will be my new response moving forward. * you have two families. one that is by chance and the ones you choose. choose wisely.

text: i keep hearing people blame victims/survivors of sexual harassment or assault saying things like, “i should’ve known that party was a bad idea,” or “she drank more than she should have.” but i just think that the consequence for a night of heavy drinking should be a bad hangover, rather than a horrible  experience of objectification and trauma! and a hangover *is* the only consequence for the privileged few, so clearly it’s *possible* for someone to drink way too much and *not* be violated. the way some people talk about it, you’d think that violation was the immediate and direct outcome of intoxication - a+b=c! i get so tired of hearing it from people who are unsympathetic towards victims/survivors, and i feel so grieved hearing it from victims/survivors themselves. but with messaging this strong, it makes sense that so many would believe it, in ways both big and small. i wonder what small ways this type of messaging still shows up in my own soul...

text:
how is sexual harassment defined under the ipc?

sexual harassment is defined under s. 354 a of the ipc as a man committing any of the following acts:.
(i) physical contact and advances involving unwelcome and explicit sexual overtures; or
(ii) a demand or request for sexual favours; or (iii) showing pornography against the will of a woman; or
(iv) making sexually coloured remarks, .
this law covers a wide ambit of acts that constitute sexual harassment, including unwanted verbal or physical advances of any kind.
.
this law is not limited by location at which the sexual harassment takes place, unlike the law to prevent sexual harassment at work places which is explained in a later section.
.
what is the punishment for sexual harassment under the ipc?

the punishment for (i), (ii) and (iii) as given above is rigorous imprisonment for a term that may extend to 3 years, or a fine, or both while the punishment for (iv) is either simple or rigorous imprisonment for a term which may extend to 1 year, or a fine, or both..
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
it is official this saturday 12/8 at @flowerpowercoffeehousenyc the @shewillspeakseries and @wide.eyes.publishing will host their first event and apart of event proceeds will go to end rape on campus (eroc @endrapeoncampus) which works to end campus sexual violence through direct support for survivors and their communities; prevention through education; and policy reform at the campus, local, state, and federal levels.

i would personally like to thank @endrapeoncampus for speaking with me @shewillspeak and really understanding what the @shewillspeakseries is trying to accomplish! i would also like to thank @endrapeoncampus for all the work they are doing! as a survivor it inspires me to see organizations that truly are there to create reform and elevate survivors voices. so make sure you come out and if you cannot we are working on how you can support/donate right now 🙏🏽

text:
i was interviewed in this @njdotcom piece written and mediated by journalist @bobbyolivier . the article includes an interactive element, so grab some headphones. it's very easy to navigate.
please search the title of this article in your internet browser or visit my website, then click the facebook icon and there you will see the link on my fb wall.

the people who need to read this are women and abused men who better start voicing their discomfort in the moment. for abusers reading this, i'm giving you the option- if you don't read this because you are sick of women's "stories", don't read further, but instead email me at info@catlondonmusic.com and i'll tell you what happened in that vacant parking lot i mention in the article. oh wait, you were there. 
stand up to creeps. i've been sexually harassed by trans people too. it's everywhere and it's real. these vultures need psychiatrists. i know men who have been abused and blackmailed too. education is key. confidence is key. if i had the confidence i have now when i was younger, hah....i would have had a much more carefree and powerful outlook on sex and this industry. these stories help young people realize they can say "no" much earlier in life than i learned.

text:
new book alert! the reflection eyes see😎. july-8-2018. myself and my 9 year old daughter wanted to share with the world how going through trauma, and from a teen mom to a dream mom can happen with love and compassion. we hope to inspire the world with our breathtaking stories of survival, and skills and tips on how to heal, and understanding the effects of trauma on the brain 🧠. it changes our dna. yes trauma has lasting effects for generations to come. stay woke👋 love the kids. 
leaders, wake up at 5am! 
leaders, drink water and tea. 
leaders, learn by first following. 
leaders, read a book a month, or week. 
leaders, give more that they get. that’s why they never want for anything. you get back 10x what you give. 
leaders do the  #28daydetoxchallenge 
leaders, are revealed in their followers.

shift your mindset and watch how you life changes❤️ when i was running into pigeons and ducks it was due to me flying to low! 
i let go of everything and everybody to rise to the top of my goals and dreams and will never stop. i hope all others understand this and will do the same! 
be bold and beautiful

text: forgiveness is not just simply saying “i forgive you”, if you want to achieve true forgiveness you have to understand and see all of the damages that circumstance has left you, and forgive that person and yourself for those damages. i was never the same after my assaults. i became an alcoholic, i became a drug addict, i’ve struggled for years to connect with people properly and be friends with men. today i have looked in the mirror and seen myself for all i am and accepted that person, accepted those damages so that i can move on from them. i have forgiven my rapist and am ready to move on with my life. thank you to all of my amazing friends who have loved me fully and completely with these damages and how you have stood by me through this process. i was ready for a breakthrough and am now ready to forgive my past to start enjoying my present ❤️❤️❤️ @woahashli @samprestonkzn @tobylizh @immollybloom @nessa.the.nerd @twylladawn @cindymyskiw @schmeekie #sexualassault #metoo #recovery #sobriety #movingon #forgiveness #damages #breakingfree #breakthrough #healing #aa #twelvesteps #thebestisyettobe

text:
i refuse to post perfect instagram photos all the time because life isn’t perfect.

so, me after an early birthday massage today. a little mess! every time i get a massage (which is not often) i’m reminded how much i love them.

they are one of my fave self love treats after i’ve worked hard in my business or been through some kinda mud.

but my mind kicks in over drive during a massage. i need to know if it's just me? 
come inside my brain: 
can’t believe it’s been so long.
okay. now just relax & enjoy this.
i think these knickers are annoying for the therapist.
oh my gosh that feels so good. 
wow. i didn’t realise how tight i am.
this is going to go so fast.
so then, just relax.
oh no, i’m starting to feel a little dehydrated.
should i quickly ask her for some water?
no irene, you’ll be fine, just breathe.
i’m not going to pass out. i’m not going to pass out.
all is good. i feel good. all is well irene.
now i’ve probably wasted about 15mins. 
good, we still on the upper body.
i have to go to post office after the massage.
crap. i still haven’t sent that email.
what in the world am i going to wear for my bridal shower?
just focus. enjoy the massage.
please god i don’t want this to end.
how embarrassing, my toe.
when is that damn toe nail going to grow back.
ouch. oh i’m so sensitive there.
what am i going to eat for lunch?
i wonder what this lovely massage lady is thinking while massaging me?
is this massage nearly over?
oh please keep going.
i’m so excited for next week.
can’t believe things are finally coming together.
i need to do this more often.
did i take my vitamins this morning?
oh no, we are up to the feet.
poor woman. that toe.
should i mention to her about my toe & what happened to it?
seriously irene, just shut it.
relax. enjoy. breathe.
what colour should i paint my nails?
are we nearly done?
a few more minutes.
she’s such a lovely lady.
i wonder what she thinks of my body.
i need to pee.

and on and on and on it went.

and then when it was over this was the end result. a thankful, grateful, mascara running mess.

is it just me?? i need some truth tellers to comment below and tell me #metoo!

text:
el 5 de diciembre marchamos por lucía, una chica que fue asesinada, violada, empalada. lucía, una chica de 16 años cuyos asesinos fueron absueltos por la justicia argentina. gente de izquierda, de centro, kirchneristas, macristas, de otros partidos, todos repudiamos esto. esta barbaridad de la justicia, abiertamente patriarcal, corrupta. en la marcha, mientras escuchaba a la mamá  de lucía  hablar, mientras todas teníamos la piel de gallina y llorábamos -de impotencia, de bronca, de tristeza, de miedo- saqué esta foto que me hizo sentir que, quizás, en no mucho tiempo, si seguimos juntas para adelante las cosas puedan llegar a mejorar 
la angustia es enorme. pero somos muchas. juntémonos.

#sevaacaer #justiciaxlucia #justiciaporlucia #niunamenos #metoo

text:
when i reflect on this past year, i have so much to be thankful for!

one of those things certainly has been the support of the media to help spread the word about the very real issues that affect so many people and damage so many lives.

special shout out to @tpatricklittle and the team at @wpri12 who helped kickoff those efforts this year. together, we filmed a powerful special feature on the issue of dating abuse and unhealthy behaviors among teens.

in the months that followed, i was able to partner with other publications, guest interview on podcasts, contribute to blogs and news articles, and truly leverage the power of the media to drive change.

and that’s only just begun... i’m so excited to have so many partners lined up for the new year, to keep making an impact, and to reach more people with each passing day. far too many people suffer and feel alone, and i can’t accept that.

text:
you are a feeling beyond imagination @officialsurbhic

this special love for my tweet is not only for me but for the entire fan family of yours across the globe.

my love, my life and my beautiful world is beautiful from inside.
this is incredible.

16 prestigious awards for playing khidkitod khoobsurat #annika & 41 in total speaks the volume about this love & craziness for you & #shivika globally. this also reflects the phenomenol journey of yours & entire team of #ishqbaaaz

you alongwith with @nakuulmehta was the 1st recipient of #heforshe award in india initiated by un women.

you always appreciated your fans in the most fascinating way for every single success achieved so far. this is incredible.

that's why for us you are the most beautiful soul on the planet.

#surbhichandna & #nakuulmehta were the face of @starplus & @startv globally.
#ishqbaaaz brought innovations in indian tv industry & has been trend setters.
you were the biggest eg. of various campaigns of starindia & starplus.
1. #nayisoch
2. #heforshe
3. #metoo

#annika carried all these initiatives & made #shivika & #ishqbaaaz a brand globally.
we will never ever forget the legacy of #shivika & #ishqbaaaz.

41 awards in 2.7 yrs tenure is an exceptional achievement for #shivika & team #ishqbaaaz

we consider #ishqbaaaz not less than a big ticket movie. level of cinematography & screenplay were mind-blowing & phenomenal in every sense.

we lived this beautiful journey since 27 june, 2016, still living & will forever cherish this journey until our last breath.

i am damn so proud to be a fan of the #surbhichandna

i love ur soul surbhi. we'll keep loving u forever and ever until our last breath.

lastly
who will forget the madness for the song "o jaana khoya khoya rehta hai, dil tadap ke kehta hai..tu hai mere jeene ki wajah.."
khidkitod pyaar kya hota hai ye humne surbhi se seekha.

with love ❤️❤️❤️ from,
divyanand kumar &
your more than 5 millions fan family on social media platforms.

#surbhichandna #annika #nakuulmehta #shivaay
#ishqbaaaz #ishqbaaazredux #gameoflove

lots of love from the bottom of my heart to
@cpchandna sir #proudfatherofadaughter &
@shashi_cp mam #proudmotherofadaughter

day 12 - repost from @m.mariposa__ 
when i was a brand new teacher, trash ass male teachers tried to go about their trash ass ways. within the first month at my new school i had been targeted by a upper grade teacher who thought i was the one - thought i would allow his behavior. i was at a loss as to how most effectively address the situation since i was the newbie. what i’ve learned is that a lot of men will make light of trespasses unless you threaten their livelihood. so i did. i wrote a detailed email to my principal and my union rep. see next image, feel free to use as template if you need to (i left the name bc idgaf, also some typos my b). no matter the field, no matter the level of education, women are continuously subjugated to deal with harassment in our day-to-day lives. i’m done with male entitlement and lukewarm allies that say nothing. do better. 💜@af3irmsf participates in 16 days of activism to amplify the voices of women of color impacted by gender-based violence. we recognize that harassment is a prevalent problem in women of color’s everyday lives because of rape culture, colonial legacies of violence, our fetishization, and our presumed accessibility. today and every day we say “stop. that was harassment.” #16daysofactivism #notyourfetish #metoo #hearmetoo #af3irm

text: let’s stand up for survivors of violence. strength and dignity are always inside every single one of us🙏🏼semalam talkshow @silalahirosi @rosi_kompastv membahas ruu penghapusan kekerasan seksual yang masih mandek di dpr, padahal payung hukum ini sangat diperlukan. saya terharu bisa kenalan dengan mbak uti yang ber jilbab merah, kalau diswipe bisa lihat. dia dulunya adalah korban karena dipaksa menikah ketika lulus sd dengan pria umur 21 tahun. sampai ketakutan dan kabur dari rumah suaminya itu, padahal mbak uti masih ingin sekolah & bercita/cita jadi polwan. sekarang mbak uti sudah menjadi survivor, kerja di koalisi perempuan indonesia, rajin turun ke desa-desa, untuk membujuk para orang tua agar tidak lagi menjalankan tradisi menikahkan putri mereka diusia anak-anak. dari masyarakat film kami berkontribusi dengan menayangkan film selama 16 hari anti kekerasan sampai 10 desember ini di @enambelasffest kalian bisa follow ignya untuk lihat jadwal. film bisa membuka mata hati dan nalar pikiran kita. teman-teman @womensmarchjkt juga akan berkumpul besok di parkiran sarinah jam 8 pagi untuk #gerakbersama ke depan istana & mendesak segera disahkan ruu penghapusan kekerasan seksual (ruupks) tersebut. ayo ikutan dan jadi bagian dari perubahan positif ini. urusan kekerasan seksual bukan cuma urusan perempuan, laki-laki juga diharapkan maju bersama sama kita semua🙏🏼💪🏼💃🏻🕺🏻☮️ #tgif #sahkanruupks #hearmetoo #16filmfestival #sisterhood #16daysofactivism #myday #empoweringwomen #womensrights #humanrights #endchildmarriage #talkshow #metoo #youarenotalone

text:
live life for the moment because everything else is uncertain! 
louis tomlinson
.
.
.
this is something i begin each day with. the way i live my life anymore. i refuse to stress the small things and have so many new amazing daily habits. living my life to the fullest and no regrets. i have never lived to put myself first, as a mother i forgot that i was still an individual person. now here i am living a little for me too. happiness of jumping out of my comfort zone has been very rewarding💕 thank you lord for the strength!

text:
this is james.

tonight on my way home from a show, i stopped off at a restaurant in chinatown. i sat at the last open table, and a few minutes after, a bunch of people came in, including a strapping young businessman named james.

as soon as he entered, the waiter told him he’d have to get take out. james ignored him and walked op to a 4-top a woman was sitting at alone and just told her to move her backpack. she did, he sat down, i guessed they knew each other. when i looked back a moment later, james had a spoon and rice, which was odd, because he’d ordered take out. i realized he was eating off the woman’s plate. she pushed it over to him without looking at him. 
at this point i got up to get take-out instead of eating in. i felt semi-responsible for the table crisis. i saw the woman paying her check, she didn’t know james. then i saw james demand some of the duck a man at the next table had. the man ignored him, then relented when he wouldn’t shut up.

so i realize this is full on #metoo #colonial bullshit. i make eye contact and shake my head “no” when he demands more duck. it doesn’t work, so i walked over and asked the woman if she knew him. look, i don’t want to be paternalistic, and i didn’t know what help to give or not give. she said she didn’t know him. i asked his name. “james.” james went to uni in nottinghamshire, he works in finance. i said i was shocked. the woman, who wasn’t s native speaker of english, didn’t hear my irony and said she wasn’t. i told james i’d never seen entitlement like his, and that he is of an ilk that made an empire. he smiled and offered a fist bump. i told him it wasn’t a compliment. then he started coughing, the woman, waiter and i feared vomit would follow, and got out of the way.

here’s james eating the rest of the guy’s duck until the dude stops him. then there’s james telling his equally tall, hot finance friend to pay fro the dude’s meal. then james got his take out, started opening it in the restaurant, then ate immediately outside the door of the restaurant.

the friend paid for the dude’s food, then said with real annoyance “he didn’t even say ‘thank you’.” truly i witnessed something as #english as nelson’

text:
friendly reminder that johnny depp is innocent
 part 3 “two days ago, amber heard’s lawyers professed their ‘outrage’ to the media that johnny depp had finally spoken in self-defense,” depp lawyer adam waldman of the endeavor group wrote in a statement to the hollywood reporter on friday. “i responded with what happens next — we will submit overwhelming evidence to a u.k. court next month that ms. heard repeatedly violently attacked and severely injured mr. depp, and then faked abuse allegations against him. ms. heard became in the process an imposter in the #metoo movement who abused the trust and experiences of real survivors for her own reputational gain.” depp’s team is previewing the evidence that it will present in the upcoming court hearing in the u.k. this fall tied to a defamation lawsuit against the sun for an article that labeled the actor a “wife beater.” “our evidence will include photographs, sworn testimony and admissions, and eyewitness accounts,” waldman wrote. “ms. heard, who has a prior arrest for domestic abuse, and her lawyers have responded to these remarkable disclosures with two days of profound silence, excepting social media posts of ms. heard wrapped in an american flag asserting: ‘we survivors…’” waldman concludes, “ms. heard’s lawyer publicly claimed ms. heard has unconsulted witnesses, but none have materialized. we would like to hear, and believe the public should hear, what, if anything, such ‘witnesses’ have to say, so that those statements may be held to account against our imminent court filings.” https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/johnny-depps-legal-team-prepares-court-hearing-amber-heard-abuse-claims-1149731

text:
💀 i've been through hell and back, and i'm not even sure where i'm anymore. there will never be a heaven for me, neither will i ever have peace. my only peace come from helping others to evolve. i eat the sins and frustrations of others. i absorb their insecurities and rebuild their faith in themselves. i make them stronger. a one-man army fighting together to help others, there were where they once were. i'm a warrior, doing my best to carry the wounded away from the battleground, even though i know it might get me hurt or kill me. but at this moment i don't even care anyone. if i can just save one more from the abyss, i will have my peace. i'll probably never experience the joy and heavenly peace others do. but i find happiness in knowing, that i helped another victim. that i made a creative mind embrace her freakyness. that i turned the flaws of one into his strengths and made him stronger than ever. i'm here to build up superhumans. soldiers of tomorrow to help others. even though it costs me everything. 💀

text:
the news, the privileged, and the universities themselves will not report on this issue; that college students feel unsafe on campus. if they do, it’s not from the perspective of those impacted by it. fortunately, there are still people who believe that is wrong. and we are those people. if you believe the same thing, go ahead and add your voice to “the room” project and, in the process, discover how your unique perspective can improve this situation.
inbox me for more details!! still, we understand that not everyone is brave enough, have the time, or comfortable to sit in front of a camera with a room full of strangers and share their voice. that is why we created the option for you to send your stories/experiences anonymously and then have other people read them aloud. while it is true that this issue is not going anywhere anytime soon, the project, however, is. so, again, reach out to find out how to get involved! 
#metoo #enoughisenough #change #pride #lgbtq🌈 #conversation #letstalk #opendiscussion #safety #university #chair #table #canon #camera #filmmaking #filmproduction #speakout #filmmakers

text:
my views on #metoo
tw: rape
a woman speaks out about rape.
she waits a couple years. "why did she wait so long?"
she speaks out immediately.
"what was she wearing?"
she speaks out anonymously.
"anonymous accusations aren't credible!"
she speaks out under her name.
"she did it for the attention."
and there she is stuck between her rapist and his supporters, with no value of her own.

text:
seriously? 
i am certainly supportive of the #metoo  movement, but i feel like things have gone way too far! the likes of harvey weinstein and bill cosby preying on women is unacceptable - men such as these deserve every bit of what they have coming to them - in fact, a lot of you know that i am a passionate advocate in my every day life for the protection of woman and children in relation to sexual abuse -  but does that mean that we have to over analyze every word to every song (including a cheeky christmas classic written a million years ago) because it could be taken offensively? 
music is story telling..for goodness sake, just enjoy the story for what it is, a story, and stop trying to make things into something they aren't just so you can jump on the socia media bandwagon! #metoobutcomeon #musicisstorytelling #gonetoofar

text:
on this day in 1989, 14 women were gunned down at a school in montreal. they were singled out for being female students in a traditionally male dominated field (engineering). they were killed by a man who believed that feminists took something from him. 🌼the following year at another canadian university, signs were hung out of dorm windows saying “no means kick her in the teeth” as a backlash against the “no means no” campaign. 🌼2 years ago the us president did not apologize for saying that when you’re a star you can do anything you want to a woman without asking. he said it was “just locker talk.” 🌼less than a year ago winemaker norman hardie was exposed for decades of sexual misconduct towards his female employees. 🌼2 days ago some dude “mansplained” the phrase “behind every good man is a good woman.” i was told that i’m too sensitive about being thought of as behind? 🌼are you tired of #metoo? yeah, me too. i’m tired of thinking of ways to not get raped. i’m tired of justifying why i call myself a feminist. i’m tired of reading about more missing and murdered indigenous women. i’m tired of listening to more and more stories about domestic abuse. 🌼i’m tired, but not defeated. 
i remember those 14 women today and #ibelieveyou . .
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.

text:
one-third of girls in afghanistan 🇦🇫, around 2.5 million girls, currently attend school 📖 according to @unwomen.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
when afghanistan was under taliban control before 2001, girls were only allowed to go to school for islamic studies. nilab and other brave girls found a way to learn in a secret basement school where they studied science and english courses by candlelight 🕯️. when the taliban learned of the makeshift school, they threatened to kill the children if they attempted to continue. but that didn’t stop nilab. with the support of her parents, she continued to study 📚 📗 📘  in secret at home.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
after the fall of the taliban in 2001, nilab and other girls were able to go to school and university. during university, nilab worked with a community ngo to end violence against women and sexual harassment. today nilab is extremely proud to support women's participation in elections through her work as a finance associate with @unvolunteers.
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
📷: undp afghanistan/ omer sadaat
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
the power of writing. writing is not only for writers, it can be a powerful therapeutic tool. similar to traditional psychotherapy, it cultivates the ability to observe our spinning thoughts and feelings, which can lead to important insights. it is a kind of mediation, where we address another consciousness and connect with who we are in the present moment. ⠀⠀
_____________________
⠀⠀ writing down your thoughts on paper with a pen also creates a mind-body-spirit connection, where you synchronise different aspects of self. ⠀⠀ _____________________
⠀⠀
⠀⠀
some of the exercise you can try: ✍🏻 free writing without censoring. do not be afraid of the “bad” thoughts. one of the main principles of acceptance-commitment therapy is to drop the struggle. so, by acknowledging and accepting our thoughts and feelings no matter how scaring or “not appropriate” they are, we can often shift them and stop their negative influence. ⠀⠀ ⠀⠀ ✍🏻 compose a letter. imagine your loved one has written to you and asked: “how are you doing, really?” a variation of this exercise is to write to someone with whom you have ‘unfinished business’ without sending it. the goal is for you to gain a clearer understanding of your own thoughts and feelings about the person or situation, put frustration into words, which can help with cognitive and emotional processing.

text:
a presenter from a radio station (that is currently under fire for alleged sexual harassment happening within the company but apparently was swept under the rug), interviewed human rights lawyer honey tan about workplace policies against sexual harassment and how sexual harassment investigations are conducted.
.
“the third thing the victim can do is lodge a police report because sexual harassment is actually a crime,” said the lawyer, highlighting section 354 and section 509 of the penal code respectively that outlaw outraging of modesty and using words or gestures intending to insult one’s modesty.
.
tan stressed the importance of respect for coworkers, no matter the workplace culture or industry.
.
“if i were an employer, i would want to err on side of caution. don't even make dirty jokes,” she said.
.
“if you're with your friends and you’re on a certain wavelength, it's fine. but in the workplace, there are different sensitivities, religions, backgrounds.
.
what may be funny to you may not be funny to them and can be quite distressing.”
.
#metoo

text:
good morning everyone, i want to share this with you all. i am going to do a live later this afternoon to chat with you all because i honestly cannot think straight!!!
but this is my personal post on my personal facebook page! 💖

personal growth is hard. growing up is hard. learning true maturity is hard. but the rewards..... the feelings..... nothing like it! 
during this very personal self healing and hope journey, i have made some incredible connections with some incredible people. women who everyday, are an inspiration, women who lift you up, women who make you believe you are doing the right thing. one of these amazing women directed me to an organisation in the us that offers a similar concept of what i am trying to achieve for young girls but is for women over the age of 18. so i decided to try my luck & apply to go. i thought not only what a great healing opportunity for my journey but also a great research & learning curve for hope. 
after months of waiting, this morning i received a phone call to say that my application was successful. so to take my journey further, i am going to the us solo & taking part in a 4 day sexual assault healing/wellness retreat. this is by far, the biggest thing i have ever done as a woman. this is a huge step for me to take. part of my ptsd is the fear of being assaulted again & so i don’t do anything by myself. yet, i want to grow, i want to mature, i want to heal. so, i am going to go. i probably will cry the whole way, may even need a valium or 2. but, i’ll do it. i’ll lead by example. i’ll take a step over the safe line. i’ll grow up just a little bit more. no one can do it for me. no one can tell me what to do. if i want this, it comes down to only me!
name: Healing Our Princess Esteem 💖💜

#winning #howitsdone — rep. #betoorourke (d-texas) met last month with former #presidentobama, just days after the texas democrat lost his senate race against sen. ted cruz (r), the washington post reported tuesday.
-
the meeting was held nov. 16 at obama's offices in washington, d.c., amid speculation that o'rourke could launch a white house bid for 2020.
-
o'rourke has received praise from several #obama's allies who said they see similarities between the former president and o'rourke.
-
obama has called o'rourke an "impressive young man" in a recent interview "the axe files" podcast, hosted by obama's former strategist, david axelrod.
-
"it felt as if he based his statements and his positions on what he believed," obama said of o'rourke's senate campaign. "and that, you'd like to think, is normally how things work. sadly it's not."
-
o'rourke was narrowly defeated last month in his effort to unseat cruz, but he is viewed as a possible frontrunner for the 2020 democratic nomination. he has said he is considering a presidential run.
-
one recent poll showed o'rourke trailing only former vice president #joebiden and sen. #berniesanders (i-vt.) among potential 2020 democratic candidates.
—

text:

text:
about 5 years ago today i was my most mentally and emotionally low. i was exhibiting symptoms of depression. the person whom had protected me mentally, emotionally and physically was no longer with me. and the person who was 'meant to' protect me was there but they weren't actually there. an incident happened. an incident which changed my life forever. it made me question everything. the incident was horrible in itself and traumatising. but the way in which a certain individual responded to it was even more traumatising. when i spoke up about what had happened, the first thing and only thing i was told was: aisha, why would he do that to you? you're not even pretty.//
//
for so long i was mentally and emotionally broken. there was a black abyss encompassing my very heart and soul. truth be told, i am still healing. i am learning how to heal. i only learnt how to heal this year. //
•
•
•
•
•

text:
had the privilege of listening to some very insightful speakers today at the #crra seminar on the topic of domestic violence. domestic violence is happening all around us. it is something that is usually unseen behind closed doors. most cases go unreported. as a property manager i am in a position where i might see the signs of domestic violence before a friend or family member would. i learned about recognizing those signs and what action i can take to help the victims. i welcome a conversation about it to anyone who would like to learn more! thank you @emerald_mgmt for helping to educate property managers and landlords across calgary about this important issue! .
.

.

i am so honored to be a contributor of words in this anthology along with many other potent writers. it's a collection and an offering. an offering of a voice - our voice - for those who have not been heard, those who have struggled to find their own words, for those who have felt isolated and alone in their experience. here, we come together to share - bleeding through words - emotions etched in ink. we are here. we have survived. and now we come together to build a legacy from the ruins of our tragedy - as we are reborn time and time again from ash. we are the phoenix. and we will forever rise. -

we will not be silenced: the lived experience of sexual harassment and sexual assault told powerfully through poetry, prose, essay, and art is now available for purchase. 
be sure to order your copy since proceeds will be donated to organizations that provide services for survivors of sexual harassment and sexual assault. 
thank you again to christine e. rey, kindra m. austin, rachel finch, candice daquin, indie blue publishing and we will not be silenced for putting this anthology together and giving us all a voice.

text:
the ‘only’ women at the top is a common problem in business. the us-based women in the workplace study published by leanin.org and mckinsey & company. findings from the survey of 279 companies revealed that “one in five women is an ‘only’”- that is, a one and only woman at senior, management or board level.
and it’s lonely being an only: “they are having a significantly worse experience than women who work with more women…they often feel on guard, pressure to perform, and left out. and they are almost twice as likely to have been sexually harassed during the course of their career.
“these negative experiences take a toll on women onlys. despite having higher ambitions to be promoted and become a top executive, they are 1.5 times more likely to think about leaving their job than women who are not onlys.” #womeninbusiness #gurls #workplace #woman #entrepreneur #femaleentrepreneur

text:
ah how important is this? i always felt like i was paying for the sins of my mother until i learned that i had complete control over my life and my choices. we don’t want the foundation to our children’s lives be our messes. that’s why it’s important to talk to your kids about your divorce, let them share their feelings and ask questions and make sure you’re there for them every step of the way. it doesn’t have to be agonizing. you just need to learn what to say. *
*
👍🏼 one thing i have always done with my kids is this: i ask them every month what they think i could be doing better as their mom: what do they need more from me? what do they think i could do better at (listening, spending alone time, fun activities)? in this space they are 100% allowed to come to me with a anything and it is my job to implement it. we don’t need to spend a lot of money to do fun things with our kids. they mostly just want your time and to see you happy and having fun with them. ♥️

text:
hello! 
my name is em! (they/them)
welcome to my senior project page! :) i am a ba visual performance major, and for my final project, i have designed a multi media/multi medium experience entitled, “!”. my major is a combination of three schools of art at suny purchase, and my project reflects that.
“!” is a show written through poems, and performed in a gallery space of visual and photographic work. 
cw:

much of my experience at purchase and as a human being has been coping and reflecting on trauma.
in a world of #metoo, #timesup, and #whyididntreport , this senior thesis will be an account of my personal experiences with r*pe and sexual assault, in hopes of seeking strength within myself, and community amongst survivors. i will be exploring gender identity, personal relationships, and memory throughout my piece, and i hope you all are willing to go on this journey with me! 
your support means the world!

text:
i’m honored the academy of art university has recognized @afn_collection in their recently published article by nina tobias, now in print and online! 
excerpt: 
anne faith nicholls has always pushed boundaries in her art and with her latest collection, she is calling on art institutions to do the same.

the afn collection, self-titled, is nicholls’ first independent art release in four years. a 2003 graduate from academy of art university’s school of illustration, the surrealist painter spent most of her career creating art to be hung in galleries and museums, from the bristol museum of contemporary art to last year’s martin lawrence gallery show in new orleans, which was when we last spoke with her.

in comparison, the afn collection is available online as a webshop featuring exclusive art offerings and female-focused collaborations, with a portion of sale proceeds donated to female-focused charities such as writegirl la and planned parenthood. this shift was motivated by nicholls’ desire to separate herself from the institutions that she said expressed, “an alarming disparity in the support, funding, camaraderie, and exposure female artists were getting compared to their male contemporaries.” “even in the best-intentioned organizations, this was across the board, at all levels, and a systemic cultural problem in the art world that i’ve found myself up against, in some way or another, for the entirety of my career,” she said. “like many, i was sick of seeing the same old dead white male artists predominantly represented in every museum, and hearing about important female curators being let go of left and right.” full article at: https://artunews.com/2018/12/05/initiating-artistic-change/

@afn_collection @academy_of_art @guerrillagirls @mollyschulps @kendramorris @sofiaenriquez @psartmuseum @whitneymuseum @centrepompidou @martinlawrencegalleries @scopeartshow 
#annefaithnichollsart #thefutureisfemale #diversity #metoo #equality #equalrepresentation #ladyart #scope #artbaselmiami #curator #collector #womenarewatching #longlivetheartlife -
“women are watching” by anne faith nicholls, 2018. available at www.afncollection.com or dm for inquires

text:
we had been working on this for a few months: today we - @feministforeignpolicy - in collaboration with the embassies of france, mali, japan, australia and canada held our #metoo event. it is important that discussions around oppressive and skewed power structures are held in all spheres of society. the fact that on the panels the embassies were each represented by their ambassadors - and in the case of mali even by a minister - and that the opening remarks were given by the german justice minister @katarina.barley showed how serious all of today’s organizers are about the topic.
.
both panels of the evening had government and civil society representatives from each country - well, continent - making for a powerful diversity.
.
it was an honour to lead through the evening and share the moderating bit with my colleague and friend colleague @vincentimmanuel .
#metoo #5c1m #france #mali #japan #australia #canada #international #berlin #power #changemakers #startup #feminism

finding your voice, speaking out against the unacceptable, and joining/adding your voice to social justice movements in whatever way speaks to you, is incredibly #empowering & life-saving & life-changing, personally & collectively. it is powerful medicine for #mentalhealth #emotionalhealth #spiritualhealth. as nayoung says: “asserting myself as a feminist became a source of intense hope, joy, and honour.”
.
#nayoungkim is a #feminist #activist & #attorney from seoul, south korea. her activist journey began in the south korean women’s movement. she went to the university of michigan law school to learn about feminist legal practice and theory from catharine a. mackinnon. nayoung is involved with #prostitution research & education, asian women coalition ending prostitution, and #af3irm @af3irm, a transnational feminist organization. her online feminist project is korea women’s liberation. she is currently translating andrea dworkin’s “woman hating” into korean. (this bio is from a #feministcurrent interview w nayoung by #meghanmurphy).
.

.

what we are naming with the impetus of #metoo is, at best, an opening to a long-term cultural reckoning to grow up humanity; to make our society more whole. we explore this with psychotherapist avi klein, who works with men and couples, and feminist journalist rebecca traister. in a room full of journalists, at the invitation of the solutions journalism network, we explored how to build the spaces, the imaginative muscle, and the pragmatic forms to support healing for women and men, now and in time. link to listen in bio –

text:
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
it is my great honor, pleasure, & privilege to announce that i will be a speaker at the women’s march on philadelphia, coordinated by philly women’s rally, on january 19, on the benjamin franklin parkway ❤️ i’ll be speaking proudly as a mental health advocate, ppd survivor, mother, and woman. 💪🏼❤️
in light of some of the recent controversy surrounding the national women’s march org. i must make this clear: as the coordinators of the women’s march on philadelphia have said it best, they are not, and never have been, affiliated with the national women’s march. as they’ve written recently, “we stand against and denounce hate and bigotry in all their forms, including recent increases in antisemitism, racism against people of color, and attacks on lgbtq people.” on january 19 i will march with and for women; i will share my story and a call to action; i will celebrate survivors; i will be a survivor; i will shout what we so often only say in a whisper; i will wear their banner, proudly. we resist. we persist. we rise. i hope to see you there 👊🏼✌🏻💪🏼
xx, b 💓💓💓

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
life in transition: how to take out your life's lessons and dump the pain

divorce? empty-nester? job change? #metoo retriggered? retirement? death of a loved one? illness? financial issues? 
life on the earth school is both physically and emotionally challenging. if you don’t know the rules you will suffer. if you are sick of suffering with being bored, depressed and tired then this is for you! find out what and why this is happening. leave with the answers you’ve been seeking! 
you will specifically learn:
• how to start looking at things so that they feed you instead of drain you
• how to get past the energy blocks that have been depressing you
• how you create your life’s happiness patterns
• how to identify, understand and let go of energetic vampires

text:
i’m honored the academy of art university has recognized my work & mission in their recently published article by nina tobias, now in print and online!

excerpt: 
anne faith nicholls has always pushed boundaries in her art and with her latest collection, she is calling on art institutions to do the same.

the afn collection, self-titled, is nicholls’ first independent art release in four years. a 2003 graduate from academy of art university’s school of illustration, the surrealist painter spent most of her career creating art to be hung in galleries and museums, from the bristol museum of contemporary art to last year’s martin lawrence gallery show in new orleans, which was when we last spoke with her.

in comparison, the afn collection is available online as a webshop featuring exclusive art offerings and female-focused collaborations, with a portion of sale proceeds donated to female-focused charities such as writegirl la and planned parenthood. this shift was motivated by nicholls’ desire to separate herself from the institutions that she said expressed, “an alarming disparity in the support, funding, camaraderie, and exposure female artists were getting compared to their male contemporaries.” “even in the best-intentioned organizations, this was across the board, at all levels, and a systemic cultural problem in the art world that i’ve found myself up against, in some way or another, for the entirety of my career,” she said. “like many, i was sick of seeing the same old dead white male artists predominantly represented in every museum, and hearing about important female curators being let go of left and right.” full article at: https://artunews.com/2018/12/05/initiating-artistic-change/

@afn_collection @academy_of_art @guerrillagirls @mollyschulps @kendramorris @sofiaenriquez @psartmuseum @whitneymuseum @centrepompidou

tweet_full:
i’m honored the academy of art university has recognized my work & mission in their recently published article by nina tobias, now in print and online!

excerpt: 
anne faith nicholls has always pushed boundaries in her art and with her latest collection, she is calling on art institutions to do the same.

the afn collection, self-titled, is nicholls’ first independent art release in four years. a 2003 graduate from academy of art university’s school of illustration, the surrealist painter spent most of her career creating art to be hung in galleries and museums, from the bristol museum of contemporary art to last year’s martin lawrence gallery show in new orleans, which was when we last spoke with her.

in comparison, the afn collection is available online as a webshop featuring exclusive art offerings and female-focused collaborations, with a portion of sale proceeds donated to female-focused charities such as writegirl la and planned parenthood. this shift was motivated by nicholls’ desire to separate herself from the institutions that she said expressed, “an alarming disparity in the support, funding, camaraderie, and exposure female artists were getting compared to their male contemporaries.” “even in the best-intentioned organizations, this was across the board, at all levels, and a systemic cultural problem in the art world that i’ve found myself up against, in some way or another, for the entirety of my career,” she said. “like many, i was sick of seeing the same old dead white male artists predomitly represented in every museum, and hearing about important female curators being let go of left and right.” full article at: https://artunews.com/2018/12/05/initiating-artistic-change/

@afn_collection @academy_of_art @guerrillagirls @mollyschulps @kendramorris @sofiaenriquez @psartmuseum @whitneymuseum @centrepompidou

text:
i really can't stay (but kitty, it's cold outside)
i've got to go away (but kitty, it's cold outside)

this evening has been (been hoping that you'd drop this)
so very nice (you want inside in five, with ice)

the magpies will start to worry (stupid, what's your hurry?)
got to chase them from the deck floor (listen to the fireplace roar)

so really i'd better scurry (idiot, i just won't hurry)
but maybe just a half a snack more (change your mind please, while i pour)

the neighbors might think (kitty, it's bad out there)
in the snow i might sink (well, at least you're longhair)

i wish i knew how (your really are a moron now)
to open this door (our indoor heat would be no more)

you ought to say, yes yes yes kitty (mind if i ignore you, fluffy?)
at least i'm gonna find some bugs to sweep (what's the sense in ending my sleep?) i really can't stay (oh kitty please do shut up)
but human, it's fun outside

i simply must go (but kitty, it's cold outside)
the answer is now (but kitty, it's cold outside)

your welcome has been (how lucky that you dropped in)
so nice and warm (to eat, sleep and keep with kitty norm)

my enemy will be suspicious (gosh that bed look delicious)
my friend will be there at the door (you mean that plastic stegosaur?) neighbors dog sure is vicious (gosh that couch look delicious)
and maybe just a little nap more (not heard a better thought before)

i've gotta get out (but kitty, you'd freeze out there)
say look at my coat (it's up to your ears out there)

you've really been grand (i scream when you claw my hand)
but don't you see? (how can you do this thing to me?) there's bound to be repeating tomorrow (think of my lifelong sorrow)
at least there will be plenty implied (if you got lost, stolen or died)
i really can't stay (you want back inside in five)

kitty, it's cold
kitty, it's cold outside

text:
i try to stay away from certain topics on social media. 
and i've questioned even posting this many times since i've seen it. 
i kept quiet when the #metoo movement came around.
kept quiet when it became an easier conversation to have, with a much more open platform.
but this was a gut shot today.
. 
i was probably 8, honestly not sure. 7? maybe 9? 
looking at my daena.
she's 8.
. 
and i would be in prison if i found out the same things had happened to her.
because people would be in p.i.e.c.e.s.
it's disgusting what people ignore, what children are told to keep a secret.
because they will.
for years.
even as an adult in college when something else happens. 
and i know i'm not alone.
hug your babies. keep them safe.
teach them to #saysomething .
#gutcheck #thisisreality #raisethemright
#raisethembetter #raisethemstrong #knowwho #knowwhere #bethechange  #keepyourbabiessafe #always #donttrustanyone

text:
let’s talk facts! 1:4 girls & 1:9 boys are the statistics surrounding victims if child sexual abuse. you or your child may not be a victim however someone in your close proximity is. iabb is here to teach the signs to the community and provide survivors with tools necessary to heal. 
_________________________________
the largest misconception about @iambeautiful_because is that in order to participate in the beauty boot camps you had to have been a victim of child sexual abuse. this is false🚫! iabb is an awareness nonprofit organization that supports female survivors of sexual but not limited to. operation beauty is specific to csa survivors. but the beauty bootcamp are all about empowering to find the beauty in their truth. whatever that may be. 
_________________________________________
our goal is to bring awareness to the community about csa and to provide preventative solutions that empower women & girls to recognize the signs of abuse and empowering them to use their voices to prevent or report abuse.

thank @konsiderdis for allowing iabb to come her show to talk about the daunting statistics & how we are here to help #childsexualabuseawareness #empowerher #beautybootcamp #metoo #survivors #triumph #iambeautifulbecause #timesup #womenempowerment #womenempoweringirls

text:
@thejimmydoreshow @bbcnews @nbcnews @anakasparianofficial @turunsanomat wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
on december 6th, 1989 a young man shot and killed 14 women at l’ecole polytechnique, before suiciding. the shooter ranted about “fighting feminism”, while specifically targeting women. this event in montreal, canada sparked conversations and action across the country and the world, to address violence against women and girls. today marks the 29th anniversary of the montreal massacre.  and in the age of #metoo - where so much change and conversation, and leadership around issues that disproportionately target women and girls has come to the forefront of our everyday lives - there is naturally a call for all of us to do better. as we think back to the tragedy of this day in 1989, we also use the as fuel to move forward to a world free of violence for all people. it is one of too many examples that continue to show us why we need to make a culture shift that prevents and responds to gender based violence, and its root causes.  part of that conversation has to be about engaging men and boys, who are most often the perpetrators of violent crime.

in response to the montreal massacre, the @wrccanada was created in 1991. they are a global movement about engaging men and boys to end violence against women and girls. and though organizations like @wrc and others have been doing great work to rethink ideas of masculinity and manhood, there is still a lot of work to be done. on this 29th anniversary, @16daysnyc is launching a #redefinemasculinity media campaign to call men and boys into the conversation around healthy masculinity. 
men commit over 90% of all violence crime. they stop talking about their emotions around 14 years old, and that is the same time they begin to suicide at 5x the rate of girls. they are more addicted to alcohol and other drugs, which are often used to cope with unfair expectations of masculinity, and they live shorter lives than women, and spend less time with their families. the expectations around manhood and masculinity that call for men to be tough and strong, and the fearless provider, are also a source of shame and harm for men. let’s talk about it! 
please share your posts about what #redefinemasculinity means to you!

@radiohelsinki @katyturnbc @huffpostitalia @foxnews bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

cnn

text:
shout-out to women around the world doing the work to heal themselves and share the love with others around them! it's not easy. we fall down so many times. but we get back up to do the work again and again because we know that we are called to a purpose which is bigger than any single moment or situation. 
tag a woman healer you know in the comments to let her know how appreciated she is! 🙌🏾 holistic practitioners, energy healers, therapists, coaches, speakers, doulas, midwives, counselors, yogis, lightworkers, herbalists, artisans, empaths, trauma survivors, wounded healers, starseeds, indigos, crystals, spirit-junkies, hsp's, prayer warriors, and seekers... 🧘🏾‍♀️if you're looking for a judgment-free space for healing through self-discovery, connection, support, and empowerment among like-minded women on a similar journey, come and check out the women's healing circle - a new (free) community on facebook.

the hero's journey is an illusion - as women, we need the support of our sisters so that we can lead a harmonious and happy life. let's lift each other up as partners in collective healing and success.

to request access to the group, click the link in bio: @rohiniwellness or visit bit.ly/iamsacredbeauty

peace+ love,
🌼dominique

the hero's journey is an illusion - as women, we need the suppo of our sisters so that we can lead a harmonious and happy life. let's lift each other up as paners in collective healing and success.

to request access to the group, click the link in bio:  or visit bit.ly/iamsacredbeauty

peace+ love,
🌼dominique

text: #31daysofsustainableliving day 6: guess what, you can now feel proud of the endless tabs you have open on your browser by switching your search engine from google to @ecosia. i learned about ecosia from @ecocult and it’s one of the easiest life changes i’ve made towards sustainability. ecosia is a b corp company based in germany that donates 80% of its profits from ad revenue to tree planting projects. it takes about 56 searches on ecosia to plant a tree (so basically one night of anxiety fueled e-comm shopping )and so far they’ve planted over 43 million trees 💚

text:
what happens when you wake up...
.
-irritable
-cranky
-moody
-no energy
-low vibe
-lost
-stuck
-sad
-stressed
-overwhelmed
-overthinking
-questioning everything
-deep in your head
-thinking your overthinking
-questioning everything
-questioning what you are doing
-questioning if you are even helping someone.
-questioning if this is your real path.
-questioning if this business is going to take off.
.
hi, welcome to my life today.
.
this is also me.
.
for so many years i'd wake up like that daily.  those were my default feelings and thoughts. it happened more during the years i was in toxic relationships.
.
this is also how my family knew me as, which has been difficult for them to see this new mary.  i don't think they quite get me still.
.
my life was a mess.
.
i've worked so much in my inner work, taken programs, courses, hiring therapists, coaches, and doing all to improve myself and be my best version daily.
.
then, my life started changing.
.
i'd wake up feeling
.
-happy
-excited
-high vibe
-driven
-passionate
-joyful
-empowered
-confident
-smiling
-grateful
-loving my life
-loving myself more
.
i can be at my best, but i can also revert back to my old patterns when i get stressed, overwhelmed, frustrated, and see things not working.
.
i'm human.
.
i was talking to my roommate yesterday and i'm like "what if i tell people how i feel some days and they judge me?", "what if they no longer like me?"
.
then, i thought...
.
my women will always be my women.
.
my tribe will love me because i'm real, raw, authentic and vulnerable.
.
they don't want perfect polly, they want imperfect and real mary that shows up authentically as she is and is not afraid to say she messes up and she also has bad days.
.
they will accept me, love me and hold space for me, because i am too healing.
.
my motto is "we all heal together."
.
healing is a daily process.  no one is 100% healed, fyi.
.
we all have fears, doubts, insecurities and judge ourselves harshly.  even the most successful people, coaches or entrepreneurs go through this.  no one is exempt from it.
.
continue 👇🏼👇🏼
