text:
these are just facts (although that new yorker cover was meant to be ironic; a pictorial binding of white psychology and it didn't bother me), none of these women would have been granted a health book at the avery imprint for exactly the reasons they *know* to be true
.

it's a *reality* that bc i'm half white and aesthetically marketable (... sellable) to an american market that avery books upheld my contact after my editors firing. if i had been browner? they would have let me go too. dark skinned black girls are all but *consciously prohibited* from representing american health. it's lunacy
.
and to be honest, i just don't engage when i hear brilliant commentaries like this. race is mutable, as i always say, and i'm essentially very much white and "privileged" in these spaces (evidenced by something as slight as my availability to embody my anger and retain a level of dignity, first based on the currancy of my mother's poor southern whitenss not my father educated black-people cash; when a dark woman *humanly* gets angry she's just cast off as "hood", bc the ghettoization of the black community makes white people feel powerful), so i listen and learn, not as a "student", but as a respectful human; it would be tacky to bond to a struggle that demands a singluar narrative, which frankly i know nothing about. it wasn't until my book was very *fucking black that meg newman lost her mind, which began with my pushback on the #metoo movement ...that disjointed excuse for a "movement"... hurt feelings *are not* sexual harrasment
.

i just happen to be hyper black in white spaces -- especially literary spaces, which is mostly informed by my open preference for black people. i am the kind of black that is a *response* to immediate environment - it changes based on the amount of whitenss in the room. black woman, particularly dark skinned black woman, *define* their environment, and it's bc of the *burden* of white fear: they hyper focus on dark skinned black woman
.

and trust, meg newman had like, *one* thought to my 600 about all this, which is not the reason i will win, but it's the reason my blackness made her disrespect her job and focus on *attempting* to play me

text:
okay hive mind! 
the new year will bring new #strongwomen to add to the series. 
so many people have given me great ideas, and i've been struggling with a way to organize, remember and keep track of them all.
i have post-its, notes jotted in my planner, notes in my sketchbook, digital files, etc. everywhere with names, quotes, reference portrait photos, etc. 
therefore, i decided to try this.
this is a padlet.  it is a digital post-it board where we can collaborate.
please help a sister out!  leave me as many ideas on who the next women should be.  i want to know who inspires you!
#inspiration #strongwoman #shepersisted #artistmom #metoo #dissent #womensmovement #makersmovement #portraiture

text_retweet:
let’s talk about break ups/heart breaks 💔
have you ever ended a relationship and gotten impulsive - e.g partying or socializing more than you usually do, cutting your hair, binging on alcohol or food or even beginning a new relationship almost immediately and prematurely? #metoo
breakups or loss of a relationship (boy/girlfriend, best friends, spouse, family) have a pretty serious domino effect on your mental health. if you have a current or pre-existing mental health condition, breakups can trigger the behavior. this means that people predisposed to anxiety and depression can be especially jolted by a breakup.

breakups can cause distorted, inaccurate thoughts that aren’t true “it was my fault” “i wasn’t good enough” “he/she never loved me” i was used” “i’ll never find love” those dark thoughts can really test your emotional resilience and often are not true. 
all breakups are different and everyone deals with them differently but it is usually not one persons fault. things sometimes just don’t work out and its okay! loosing a relationship can cause one to lose their ability to be vulnerable with others (aka shutting down and being guarded) but when you do this, you deprive yourself of love. 
tips on getting over a breakup:
1. don’t take any drastic measures because these behaviors can have long-term negative results.
2. keep your routine. get up and do what you’d usually do before the break up (not easy i know!). try. 
3. communicate and stay in touch with those who love you. it reminds you that you are loved regardless.
4. find something that makes you feel good in the moment. i recommend exercising. 
5. change your thought patterns by reframing the negative into the positive, this will gradually increase your happiness while gaining perspective on why the relationship wasn’t the right one for you. 
overall, sometimes a break up is exactly what you need! repost and help a broken woman out there out! #happymonday #breakups #loss #grief #depression #anxiety #suicideprevention #mentalhealth #nycpsych #njpsych #psychmd #peptalk #heartbreaks #mentalhealthawareness #psychiatry #mind

text: est ce que t'es une petite pute ou une salope ? est ce que t'es une chaudière ou une fille facile ? est ce que tu suces ou que tu te mets à genoux ? est ce que t'es bonne ou juste baisable ? est ce que tu veux que je te fasse la petite sœur ou le petit frère ? est ce que t'as un numéro ou un facebook ? dis c'est quoi ton nom ? ton nom putain. mon nom putain c'est femme. femme. femme. et je suis peut être jeune ou vieille, grosse ou mince, fougueuse ou révoltée, douce ou touchante, je suis peut être forte ou fragile, jolie ou originale, généreuse ou réservée, enceinte ou célibataire, hétéro ou homo, mon nom est femme. de mon plus jeune âge au dernier je suis femme. et moi femme, tu me dois le respect. que tu sois jeune ou vieux, gros ou mince, fougueux ou révolté, doux ou touchant, fort ou fragile, joli ou original, généreux ou réservé, papa ou célibataire, hetero ou homo, je ne suis ni ta pute ni ta salope, ni ta chaudière ni ta fille facile, ni la bouche ouverte ni à genoux, ni bonne ni baisable, ni accessible par téléphone ou internet, ni prête pour un deuxième avec toi, et je ne suis pas ta femme. surtout pas ta femme. ce soir, je suis femme, mille fois plus que les autres jours, et maman, le cœur touché par le récit de la fille de @bonjourlesfleurs et je vous invite, femmes, à écrire ce qui vous révolte. non pas pour taguer un #metoo de plus, mais pour dire, pour écrire, la solidarité féminine et prouver que dans la laideur du harcèlement, il y a aussi la magie du soutien. alors, #desmotspourunefleur c'est ce soir, cette semaine, ce mois. alors, à vous. #encolere #stopauharcelement #harcelementderue #protegeonsnosenfants #femme #feministwitch #sororité #solidarité

text:
let’s talk facts! 1:4 girls & 1:9 boys are the statistics surrounding victims if child sexual abuse. you or your child may not be a victim however someone in your close proximity is. iabb is here to teach the signs to the community and provide survivors with tools necessary to heal. 
_________________________________
the largest misconception about i am beautiful because is that in order to participate in the beauty boot camps you had to have been a victim of child sexual abuse. this is false🚫! iabb is an awareness nonprofit organization that supports female survivors of sexual abuse but not limited to. operation beauty is specific to csa survivors. but the beauty bootcamps are all about empowering women and girls to find the beauty in their truth. whatever that may be. 
_________________________________________
our goal is to bring awareness to the community about csa and to provide preventative solutions that empower women & girls to recognize the signs of abuse and empowering them to use their voices to prevent or report abuse.

thanks konsiderdis radio for allowing iabb to come her show to talk about the daunting statistics & how we are here to help #childsexualabuseawareness #empowerher #beautybootcamp #metoo #survivors #triumph #iambeautifulbecause #timesup #womenempowerment #womenempoweringirls

text:
5 am
friday morning
thursday night
far from sleep
i'm still up and driving
can't go home
obviously
so i'll just change direction
cause they'll soon know where i live
and i wanna live

got a full tank and some chips
it was me and a gun
and a man on my back
and i sang "holy holy" as he buttoned down his pants
you can laugh
it's kind of funny things you think
at times like these
like i haven't seen barbados
so i must get out of this

yes i wore a slinky red thing
does that mean i should spread
for you, your friends, your father, mr. ed

me and a gun
and a man
on my back
but i haven't seen barbados
so i must get out of this

and i know what this means
me and jesus a few years back
used to hang and he said
"it's your choice babe just remember
i don't think you'll be back in 3 days time
so you choose well"
tell me what's right
is it my right to be on my stomach
of fred's seville

me and a gun
and a man
on my back
but i haven't seen barbados
so i must get out of this

and do you know carolina
where the biscuits are soft and sweet
these things go through you head
when there's a man on your back
and you're pushed flat on your stomach
it's not a classic cadillac

me and a gun / tori amos
.
.
.

text:
being vulnerable with words has always come naturally to me. embracing my sexuality and body has not. i’m not going to say the only way you’ll feel comfortable in your skin is when you can throw a bathing suit on and not feel shame or embarrassment. that feeling comes and goes whether we want it to or not. falling in love with your body begins with accepting every curve, scar, lump, and bump that is you and respecting your body in all of its states. this love comes when you aren’t afraid to show your confidence. it comes when you are willing to share that beauty with others in the hopes that they will too. the hurt ends when the shame from wandering eyes and past experiences have been put to rest, the embarrassment has subsided, and the love for yourself has re-written the image you had of yourself.
you not only welcome your differences but you allow them to shape you as a human moving forward.

text:
woop woop här kommer en hel drös med tips på hårda julklappar från världens bästa emma knyckare! • • • ”mot patriarkatet” av clara henry. clara är kanske det bästa som har hänt mig. hennes böcker till min 13-åriga bonusdotter är den bästa investering jag gjort. samtidigt får bonussonen läsa hampus nesvolds ”ta det som en man” och sedan kan dom byta böcker med varandra. hejja denna djupt begåvade generation som ger oss normkritiskt och underhållande diskussions-underlag hemma. • • • ”mellan raderna” av jenny nordlander. tusentals kvinnor slöt samman under #metoo, samtidigt satt jenny med färdigt manus om kvinnors villkor inom journalistbranchen. tack för denna bok. • • • ”lisbet och sambakungen” av emma karinsdotter.
emmas bok är den varmaste och roligaste bok jag läst för mitt barn. det har tillochmed varit roligt att göra läggningen. äntligen en barnbok om tokiga, rimliga vuxna som jag kunde identifiera mig med. • • • ”vi ska ha barn” av marie björk. en handbok i jämställt föräldrarskap som riktar sig till båda föräldrarna. hade vi läst denna när jag var gravid hade jag antagligen inte behövt skriva min föräldrabok ”hit med flaskan.” • • • ”det heliga jävla moderskapet” 
en samling skamlösa berättelser om moderskapet. min bibel och helt genial. en rimlig bok som alla borde få på mödravårdscentralen. • • • ”en apa i rågsved” av anna suvanna davidsson. 
annas debutroman är en skildring av en kass relation, att våga bryta upp för att tillslut våga vara sig själv utan att be om ursäkt. 
den gav mig hopp. • • • ”moder justitia” av ida eklöf. en samling texter/dikter som är roliga, rätta och smashing fantastiska. 
jag är så glad över att ha få upptäckt även lyrik. detta tack vare yolanda bohm och hennes bok ”ikon” som rätt från hjärtat daskar ut dom mest smärtsamma och roligaste orden på ett magiskt sätt.
name: Brombergs Bokförlag

text:
just because you’re a sensual person, doesn’t mean you owe it to anyone. just because someone’s generous with you, doesn’t mean you’re obligated to return the favor. the luminosity of your erotic nature can light a room, but like a lantern, you can still have a boundary of protection that will serve to keep your flame aglow. you get to choose who comes close to warmth of your sensual fire. your capacity to give and receive in sustainable health increases the more you *trust yourself* to protect your sacred flame. 🔥 
exploitation is the second core wound in rebloom. the antidote? your natural blueprint of health? sovereignty. healthy boundaries. keeping your temple healthy, happy, holy. 
when we have histories of exploitation, our connection to *self-trust and healthy limits* often erodes. we give away too much, too fast. or afraid of being taken from, we wall off, become untouchable, dim our light completely.
if boundaries are challenging for you, perhaps try this:
put your hands on your hips or your pelvis. sway a bit. whisper these words inwardly or outwardly...
i get to decide what comes in and what stays out.
i keep my temple healthy, happy, holy.
i say yes to...
yes...
yes...
yes...
i say no to...
no...
no...
no...
your body knows. go on, listen.
❤️
if you want to learn some seriously effective skills for helping repair boundary violations (for both yourself & your clients) rebloom your business has got the goods. 6 months of intimate & in-depth personal & group mentorship for becoming an epic trauma-informed guide. head to the 1st link in my profile to learn more and apply. ❤️
#rebloomthebook #prayer #metoo #healthyboundaries #traumainformed #sexualhealing

text:
кто вы, ингмар бергман?⠀
⠀
12 декабря в 18:30 в zal #2 галереи «арт-беларусь» пройдет лекция «пересматривая классика: кто вы, ингмар бергман?». на примере лент из ретроспективы «уикенды с бергманом» киновед и программный директор кинофестиваля «лістапад» игорь сукманов расскажет о том, как творчество шведского режиссера продолжает влиять на личность современного зрителя.

спустя сто лет после смерти «великого шведа» настало время заново переосмыслить влияние на кинематограф одного из главных авторитетов, режиссеров и мыслителей хх века. в новом столетии зазвучали иные голоса, появились новые мастера, направления и стили. постдок, постмодерн, движение #metoo… «выжил» ли бы бергман в нашу эпоху? какое место сегодня занимают ленты мастера, который вывел из «утиной заводи» скандинавское кино? сохранили ли его картины ясность и четкость мысли? способны ли они совершенствовать нас?

игорь сукманов предлагает порассуждать о том, можно ли по-прежнему считать ингмара бергмана актуальным режиссером, изменяющим умонастроение зрителя.

вход свободный, необходима регистрация. (ссылка в описании профиля)

12 декабря, 18:30, zal #2 (второй зал галереи арт-беларусь)

до встречи на лекции!

___

12 декабря в 18:30 в zal  галереи «арт-беларусь» пройдет лекция «пересматривая классика: кто вы, ингмар бергман?». на примере лент из ретроспективы «уикенды с бергманом» киновед и программный директор кинофестиваля «лістапад» игорь сукманов расскажет о том, как творчество шведского режиссера продолжает влиять на личность современного зрителя.

спустя сто лет после смерти «великого шведа» настало время заново переосмыслить влияние на кинематограф одного из главных авторитетов, режиссеров и мыслителей хх века. в новом столетии зазвучали иные голоса, появились новые мастера, направления и стили. постдок, постмодерн, движение  «выжил» ли бы бергман в нашу эпоху? какое место сегодня занимают ленты мастера, который вывел из «утиной заводи» скандинавское кино? сохранили ли его картины ясность и четкость мысли? способны ли они совершенствовать нас?

игорь сукманов предлагает порассуждать о том, можно ли по-прежнему считать ингмара бергмана актуальным режиссером, изменяющим умонастроение зрителя.

text:
good morning modern abolitionists! 
this week’s #thursdaythoughts :
so many people think of human trafficking as unstoppable and hopeless; they make this an excuse to sit back and do nothing.
“great, you helped one person, what are you going to do about the rest of the world?”
however, isn’t the life of one child, one human, worth the effort? of hoping in the face of despair? 
pimps and exploiters do not value their lives—that’s how these human beings are able to live with what they’re doing. if you see these victims as worthless, as not worth saving, then how are you any different? .
.
.
🎞: @pricelessmvmt 👩🏻: @madeleine_jade1 .
.
.
#boomdropthemic #endhumantrafficking #endslavery #humansave #shesworthit #metoo #hertoo #himtoo #everylifematters #ourchildrenourfuture #changetheworld #homeofthebrave #landofthefree #humantrafficking #endexploitation

text:
o programa das nações unidas para o desenvolvimento (pnud) se uniu, mais uma vez, à campanha anual de 16 dias de ativismo contra a violência de gênero, iniciada no domingo (25), dia internacional para a eliminação da violência contra as mulheres, e que termina em 10 de dezembro, dia internacional dos direitos humanos. o tema da campanha é “pinte o mundo de laranja: #meescutetambém”, que segue o rompante de movimentos globais como o #nenhumaamenos (#niunamenos), #metoo e #timesup para trazer ao primeiro plano as vozes de mulheres e meninas que sobreviveram à violência e que estão lutando por seus direitos diariamente. além disso, a proposta das nações unidas é expressar apoio às vítimas de assédio sexual e de outros tipos de abuso, muitas das quais vieram a público ao longo do ano passado para denunciar agressões e agressores.

#onumujeres #onumulheres #vistalaranja

text:
15 milionë vajza adoleshente në të gjithë botën kanë rënë pre e marrëdhënieve seksuale të dhunshme në një fazë të caktuar të jetës së tyre.

intesa sanpaolo bank albania i bashkohet fushatës me sloganin: “më dëgjo edhe mua!” duke i bërë thirrje çdokujt të inkurajohet për të organizuar aktivitete me lëvizjet e grave, me të mbijetuara të dhunës, me aktiviste të mbrojtjes së të drejtave të grave duke krijuar sinergji për mundësi dialogu mes aktivistëve, politikë-bërësve dhe publikut.

text:
artist's bio update💚🌸 originally from nyc, mair prudence is a writer, sculptor, and yoga/reiki therapist living and working in litchfield county, ct  usa
"each sculpture is uniquely hand-built, stone-burnished, proprietarily glazed; ultimately hand-buffed using soy & bees waxes. 
the inception of each piece has always been a necessary, urgent; innate sense of first seeking peace as a teenager, then 35 years later... refuge. as an adult, the impetus, at first, was to teach my then teenage daughter how to make a hand-built vessel  the creation of each piece has been a lifesaving practice of peace, prayer, and meditation. prayer for me has been informed  mainly by buddhist dharma.  i do, however, subscribe to an eclectic blend of all the world's esoteric spiritual traditions.  the process of creating each piece is a practice of emptiness for me.
the glazes are also unique...hand-made...using stones gathered along the shores of new england beaches & islands...for now:).
the glaze recipe was given to me by a native american man upon admiration and inquiry of his work. he would gather stones from the shores of lake michigan "...before the great white comes... ". he gave me his indigenous formula explicitly to "please the ancestors."
i hope they are pleased." mair💚🌸 #artist #art #sculpture #sculptor #healingarts #artheals #stonesrock #refuge #meditation #keepgoing #remainconscious #creativity #practiceforlife #createforlife #dothething #zen #zenart #mentalhealth #mentalwellness #lymedisease #domesticviolence #violenceagainstwomen #metoo #timesup #emergingartist #yogaart #emergingwomen #editor #publish #publishing

text:
national day of rememberance and action on violence against women, an opportunity to remember the women murdered on a montreal campus in 1989 and to recognize that gender-based violence is an ongoing problem.
.
in a past life, i spent well over a year writing this very short piece and even just seeing the title again makes my heart race, fingers tingle. the experiences of violence themselves were scary, but "going public" with the fact that they happened was even more terrifying. this was well before #metoo , even before jian gomeshi broke headlines, and before this was part of workplace policies and conversations. in the title, i point to one of the last and only papers published decades earlier, by quoting a supervisor's response to his female grad student when she revealed that she was raped at gunpoint during her field research. getting raped does not make you a fool, it goes without saying... right?
.
on the day that this went public, i was nearly debilitatingly concerned that i'd lose my credibility as a scholar who cared deeply about the results and meaning of my research for the communities i worked in. this very problem is what i was trying to challenge in the paper itself, and most responses that day and to this day have been incredibly supportive. a department and a faculty committee were formed, the paper was even brought to the international science council. but, what has stuck to my heart was a comment from a colleague who said "i'm not surprised. you look people in the eyes when you talk to them, and you're so friendly", as though he could legitimize violence against me, as a result of... well, being me.
.
we need to keep doing better, so that we --as humans, but particularly as women, trans women, and women of colour -- can not only be more safe pursuing our dreams but also feel more safe talking about our experiences of violence.
.
#december6 #forgive #healyourheart #healyourbody #healcommunity #forgiveness #canada

text:
ok brother,
.
you’re not going to like this.
.
but you didn’t sign up for this  friendship just so i could blow smoke up your ass, did you?
.
nah, you called me in to keep it real. so here it is:
.
.
.
.
you are a misogynist.
.
yes. you.
.
now, before you go getting your tighty-whities in a wad with your, “not me!’ and “not all men!” bullshit, just hear me out.
.
first, it’s not your fault you were born a dude in a world dominated by men and patriarchal systems. there’s no blame here.
.
second, if you haven’t admitted to yourself that you carry some lady-hating programs deep in your psyche—and actually started actively dismantling them—then you are most likely falling short of the most exquisite relationships you can have with women.
.
take a breath with that.
.
now, the great news is that, no matter how much you may have already addressed this issue, you can always dig deeper and find subtler layers of objectification and prejudice in there. the really cool part is that, the better you understand women, the richer and sexier your relationships with them will be. .
and you can still be a fucking beast of a man and be sensitive to the value and experience of the feminine.
.
you can keep your balls while you dismantle your misogyny.
.
i promise.
.
and the safer a man you become the safer the whole world becomes for women (and men too)! everybody wins when we face this stuff.
.
#sorrynotsorry,
.
a man who cares
.
p.s. if you are a woman reading this, odds are really good that you're a misogynist too. that somewhere along the way you were also trained to hate and/or devalue the feminine. just syain'.
.
.
.
#misogyny #shadowwork #metoo #healing #relationship #gettingfree #hardtruth #nobs #nobscommunication #keepinitreal #masculine #feminine #evolution

text:
happy independence day dear finland! ❤️ i’m so proud to call you my country, and even though we live in a long distance relationship, i think it’s a really good one. your language makes my accent obvious and your way of arranging healthcare and education has given me the tools and safety to go and explore the world and make it mine. looking at you from a distance, it really is clear - i’m one of the biggest luckiest lucky ducks on earth. .
.
i’m also very happy to have a name that’s very finnish! aino is originally a lady in the finnish national epic, kalevala. she’s a lady who would have most definitely benefitted from the #metoo movement, and even though her story is sad (look it up), it binds me personally to the finnish cultural history. .
.
aino is pronounced ‘i know’ (or, that’s the closest that i can easily explain it to an american), and having a strange name often leads to a nice conversation about where i’m from. so far, all of those conversations have been very positive, and i’ve learned to accept that it’s the small talk i do where ever i go, almost every day. .
.
and it’s easy to talk about finland, because i’m so proud of it! i’m also happy of my life here in the usa, so what does it make me? a proud immigrant!!! 😁
.
.
#proudtobeanimmigrant #finland #independence  #kalevala

text:
look out! it's the #funpolice coming to ruin christmas songs & children's shows near you! 
look out! it’s the left’s fun police! 
in the #metoo era, any remote suggestion of men “taking advantage” of innocent young women must be wiped away from history. “baby, its cold outside,” a classic christmas song for over 50 years, must be banned from the airwaves! it doesn’t matter that 94% of the radio stations listeners said no to the ban, the radio station caved to the 6% that voted the christmas song is inappropriate. outraged feminists that make up 6% can dictate to the majority what they can and cannot listen to at christmas?

it is a cold and lonely christmas when the #metooers are huddled near the space heater with their six cats, drinking wine and eating that pizza for one as the resentment against men festers inside them. if they can’t have fun, then no one deserves to have fun.

stop in the name of the fun police! rudolph you are “problematic”, the fun police pronounced about “rudolph, the red-nosed reindeer” the favorite christmas show of millions of children around the world. seems rudolph’s dad was bullying him and donner was a racist bigot against “red-nosed” reindeer. presumably this fell in the same category as atrocities committed against native americans. who knew?

no justice! no charlie brown thanksgiving! charlie brown and the whole gang (including that bigot snoopy) were accused of bigotry and racism against the only black child in the “hood” when he was seated across from the gang. the fun police claimed this was blatant racism when actually he got the best seat in the house. where’s black lives matter when you need them?

how dare you! you are not inclusive! the fun police charged the “victoria secret” show featuring beautiful women dressed as angels in skimpy outfits. where are the trans gender women? where are the lesbians? where are the plus, plus size models? they need representation too!

it comes down to this. will you continue to let a small minority of nagging scolds ruin your holidays and relationships? who made them the moral authority in this country and why do companies listen to them and cave in? because they are loud and persistent

text:
on december 6, 1989, 13 female students and a female administrator at l'école polytechnique de montréal were murdered because they were women. the shocking impact of their deaths led parliament to designate december 6 as a national day of remembrance. nearly 30 years later, the effects of this tragedy continue to be felt and women remain targets because of their gender.
. 
the national day of remembrance and action on violence against women is about remembering victims; it is also a time to take action. we each have the opportunity and the responsibility to stand up against misogyny, sexism, and hate — and it starts with creating a culture of respect.
today we are reflecting on the three women who are victims of femicide in our region; wendy allan, heeley rae balanga, sandra finn. 💜🕯️🕯️🕯️💜 .
.
.
#metoo #16daysofactivism
#ksac #femicide #genderviolence #genderbasedviolence #timesup #webelievesurvivors #survivors #kawarthasexualassaultcentre

text:
~ stepping into my masculinity with soooo much shame ~
⠀⠀
in the past, i’ve struggled with my personal power as a “masculine” man. i was ridiculed and chastised at a young age for my love of women and my desires to court and romance the girls/women i was interested in. ⠀⠀
that guilt still exists today (!) and i am working to banish them from my reality:
⠀⠀
the words of my siblings calling me conceded because i took pride in my physical appearance. this no more from here on out!
⠀⠀
the guilt i felt from my peers for liking multiple women and loving them all deeply at the same time. only now to know that’s very normal and can be identified as polyamorous. i will breath and sink deeper into my multi-loving soul.
⠀⠀
the shame that comes with being a man in 2018 due to the poor actions on the selected few white men in power from decades before my time. your story is not mine! ⠀⠀
and to the women who don’t recognize me as an ally… i will no longer hold space for your criticism and judgment. my life is mine to live and i know who i am!
⠀⠀
to the men with fragile egos fight me or talk to me... i can do both fluidly and very well. ⠀⠀
i am a man of love, passion, and kindness. i love beautiful women, sports, art, money, freedom, deep spiritual consensual connections, tantra, so much more! ⠀⠀
i am divine masculine. hear me roar. #manup
name: Divine Masculine • Innergrowth

text:
our past, if listened to carefully provides us a roadmap of our future. it allows us to reflect, re-adjust, amend, heal and progress. 
29 years ago today, 14 women fell victim to an act of gender based violence at école polytechnique in montreal. 
in 1991, the parliament of canada declared december 6th as the national day of remembrance and action on violence against women.  today we remember their names. #riseuparchive

text:
the year was 1993 and i pranced around campus in 6” stilettos while all the girls where in high top reebok’s.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
::⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
my hair was every color under the rainbow before it was cool.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
::⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i had a big ol’ badonkadonk and snatched waist before surgeries and injections.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
::⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i was the campus nail tech doin crazy designs on everybody’s nails.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
::⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
and still managed to stay on the dean’s list.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
::⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i was ahead of my time.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
::⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i was walking around with everything it took to make it.
::⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
but the secret i was carrying of being raped just one year earlier was an anchor pulling me down into an ocean of depression and shame and self-loathing. no one could’ve told me i was worth anything.⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
::⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
that’s why i know that talent and hard work and looks will never replace solid and consistent healing. you must do the work. you have to be willing to stop fearing the pain will kill you and start using it as the ultimate source of your power.  #tbt #virginiastateuniversity #vstate #harrishall #healblackwomen #tbt
name: J E N N I F E R   A R N I S E

text:
why are there so few women at the top?
opportunities for career progression appear to be limited for female colleagues and i wonder if maternity discrimination has a part to play here.
professional development for women in the workplace diminishes as they edge ever-closer to child-bearing age; women with and without children – as well as those with no intention of having children – are viewed with suspicion and as a result unfairly discriminated against.
one in five uk employers admitted that if a woman is pregnant or has children it impacts decisions about whether to promote them. if you need help with creating family friendly policies drop us a msg.

text:
🕊 beyond the bruises
_
when i was 19, trembling on the phone telling the cops i’d been hurt, i never would have thought that someday i would be campaigning against domestic violence. i never thought i would travel to cambodia. i never thought i would help other women find strength. i never thought i would make a career out of fitness or dance. i never thought i would help other women learn to love themselves. and i certainly never would have thought that lil ol me could actually make a difference.
but then one day i chose to believe. that i would. that i could. and so i did.
i am immensely grateful for everyone who has donated to my campaign of running 24km for $2400. your koha will go to @nca_newcambodianartists . they do such important work challenging gender stereotypes and cultural restrictions, breaking boundaries for cambodian performing artists and empowering women through dance. 
as a huge cherry on top, half of the proceeds from the #etlforgood project run through @eattrainlovesg will also go to nca. 
arohanui everyone, you have made the totally scary act of verbalizing (you know what they say ...if it’s on social media..) what had happened to me absolutely worthwhile. ‘your greatness is not what you have.
it’s what you give.’

text:
year in review – mar 2018

chasm
presented by @thetanknyc
conceived and performed by @patekrebecca
directed by meghan finn

chasm looked at the events at the 2014 @americanrealness festival during her piece "ineter(a)nal f/ear" that led patek to leave the contemporary dance/performance art world for a career in medicine. in her satirical and ingenious comedic style, patek told her side of the story, why what happened was fundamentally unjust, and reflected on a wider problem in the contemporary performance world still yet to face its own #metoo reckoning.

###

join our @classy_org campaign to raise $35k before december 20! this year, your contribution can get you premium access to 2019 events.

make your tax-deductible contribution today and support the tank's programs for emerging artists in nyc: http://www.jointhetank.org

meghan finn and @grushhour, co-artistic directors
#thetanknyc
#jointhetank

text_retweet:
・・・repost @nadiakyba 
i remember this day in 1989 so clearly. i was in my first year at u-vic. studying political science. like most students i didn’t have a tv in my little student apartment above john’s place - just cbc radio who reported on this event happening at another university across the country.
.
14 women. smart, ambitious women studying engineering - a traditionally male subject. they were separated from the men and shot while the shooter made angry comments about women.
.
every year on this day i wonder how much has changed. i still hear misogyny in the music that is popular today - in fact it is much worse than it was in 1989. but according to the kids it is fine as long as you don’t say the n word. is it though?
.
i hear about widespread sexual assault on university campus’ across canada. not a day goes by that i don’t worry about my own daughters. one at university - living on campus.
.
the other i have weekly arguments with about whether or not she is allowed to ride her bike in the dark to and from basketball practice at a school that is 800 meters from our house. she just wants to ride her bike and i am terrified of the dark path that will lead her there.
.
backlash and comments about how the #metoo movement has “gone too far” continue to shock me.
.
i dunno.
.
#nationaldayofremembranceandactiononviolenceagainstwomen

text:
herd, meet our december #eers plawyright, scott c. sickles!
...
his plays have been performed in nyc, across the united states, and internationally in canada, australia, the uk, hungary, singapore, and lebanon. nonsense and beauty, his biographical drama about e.m. forster, makes its world premiere at the repertory theatre of st. louis in march 2019.
...
other plays include composure (winner, 2016 new york innovative theatre award; 2018 lambda literary award finalist), intellectuals (smith & kraus’ new playwrights: best plays of 2007), moonlight & love songs (gayfestnyc 2013), lightning from heaven (1999 beverly hills theater guild/julie harris playwriting award), perfecting the kiss (dc capital fringe, 2018).
- published short plays: beautiful noises (smith & kraus), murmurs (samuel french), turtles and bulldogs (applause).
- this fall, three of his plays make their debuts: badger and frame at emerging artists theatre; the bedroom summit in the #metoo plays, and outpost at otherworld theater’s paragon festival.
- he has received four consecutive writers guild of america awards for the daytime drama “general hospital,” and six emmy award nominations. member, dramatists guild, new play exchange. to learn more about scott and his work visit, www.scottcsickles.com
...
we are honored to explore scott's piece, mariana's trench as our december eers piece! to learn more, visit our site >>>http://www.elephantroomproductions.com/elephant-ears-reading-series/
@doughboynyc @doughboynyc

text:
people need to understand that it is fucking hard to report!

first, you are afraid to speak these awful words. you do not want to say or even hear these terrible things done to you. you are afraid of the reaction of the people. will they believe you? will they accuse you? will they say "you were asking for it"? you are afraid because they will not be able to understand it. you are also afraid of the questions of the police. you are afraid of the tears of your parents. you are afraid of the trial because you will have to see the person who assaulted you again. you are afraid that the jury will believe him and not you. you are afraid that he will not be punished.

never judge a survivor for not reporting. it takes a lot of strength, courage and above all support to take this step. and of course it takes a lot of strength to survive this terrible experience! and no one can empathize with the fear a survivor carries.

it's not easy to say, "i was raped" or "my father abused me". it's not easy to speak your trauma aloud.

#battlefortomorrow #feminist #metoo #nomore #trauma #assault #womendontoweyoushit #timesup #whyididntreport #rape #sexualharassment #feminism #resist

text: on my path of healing, one of my biggest struggles was being told i should forgive what happened. forgive the person(s). a lot of my pain was trying to come to peace with how this was helpful.  really? in addition to being traumatized, i’m expected to be responsible for this for healing?? how does that not perpetuate victimhood, i wondered? it felt unempowering to even consider. it made me feel so many feelings but none of them gave me peace. i wanted to feel strong. the greatest gift i gave to myself was to realize i do not have to forgive the person/situation. it is not a requirement. ever!!! i only needed to forgive myself. to give myself permission to acknowledge my pain and my reactions to it. shifting my pattern of thinking to one focused on self-love was the beginning of focusing on my future. that part felt hopeful and gratifying. it was a relief to begin to let go of the who and why and what happened that was just a giant loop lost in the past ...and turned my attention forward. what a relief to begin to feel responsible for just me. i stopped feeling bad for how i reacted in my pain and simply acknowledged her as a different, younger version of me trying to figure things out. sometimes it isn’t pretty. it’s all part of the repair process. it’s growth....that’s okay. i’m okay. choosing to accept and love myself was the most empowering decision i made for me. self-forgiveness is the doorway to healing. it is powerful. it is strength. 💗💪🏻💗👍💗 #yougotthis #selflove #itsajourney #selfforgiveness #healing #imokay #metoo #trauma #repair #personalwork

text:
"humans and flowers are alike. even we take time to grow, even we bloom and even we wither." i quoted her sitting at the balcony.

her apartment was on 21st floor and that was the best thing because the sky, the sun and the moon were clearly visible from her balcony as there was no adjacent skyscraper kissing her window.
she had brewed my favorite coffee and we were just sitting, looking at the clear sky which had turned crimson.
.
"but humans are independent and flowers are not, they require sunlight, water etc inoder to grow." i again stated trying to figure out the dissimilarities.
.
"even we are dependent, we require love, care and affection to bloom." she corrected giving her innocent smile.
.
"i require maggie with extra cheese, just now or i will wither!" i ordered her.

she hesitated at a first but prepared with all her extra love and cheese in it. it was a lovely evening indeed. i looked at the clock at it was still 2.47 am and the memory which ran in my mind made my eyes drenched with tears. 
i turned sides, and thought she was right. she was right when she said it was my fault of ignoring her and give her time according to my wish. she was right when she told me that love is not being a honey bee and sucking the nectar in the form of love from one flower to flower instead staying back to the roots in every sun, in every rain and in every storm. i knew i was shrinking like a cheap cloth after the first wash. i knew i was not growing with the lack of love, care and affection.

next morning, i called her up
.
"hello ma'am can i book a table for two in your balcony for 6pm?" i tried to keep it light.
.
"you are dependant just like my flowers." she replied.
.
"yes, for your love and for...."
.
"for maggie with extra cheese." she giggled.
.
.

darshan sanghvi.
(@darshansanghvi28)
.
.

text:
কিছু দিন ধরে খুব আতংকে আছি,একজন আমাকে বেশ বিরক্ত করতো বিভিন্ন ভাবে,সেদিন হঠাৎ ডাইনিং'র বেসিনে মুখ ধোবার সময় দেখলাম সে পাশের বাসার ছাদ থেকে আমায় দেখতে উঁকি দিচ্ছে!প্রতিবাদ করতে আওয়াজ তুলতে চেয়েছিলাম,কিন্তু পারি নাই!আমার মন বলল,"না,এখন আওয়াজ তুলো না,তুমি এখন রাস্তায় একলা চলো,যদি তোমার মুখখানা মানুষরূপী এই বখাটে ঝলসে দেয়?যদি সে তোমার স্বত্তাকে কেড়ে নেয়?"আমার আমি আমায় থামিয়ে দিলো,কিন্তু আমি জানি,এই অত্যাচার এখানেই শেষ হয়ে যাবে না,এমন অমানুষ আমার আশেপাশে প্রতিনিয়ত ঘুড়ে বেড়াবে।কেমন করে সেই অমানুষদের সাথে আমি পারবো?আমি তো এখন রাস্তায় একলা চলি!
কিছুদিন আগের এক ঘটনা-আমি আমার বাবা'র সাথে ঢাকা মেডিকেলে এক কাজে গিয়েছি,বাবা একজন পরিচিত ডাক্তার এর সাথে কথা বলছিল,আমি ওয়েটিং রুমে বসে,হঠাৎ দেখি পর্দার ধারে একজন অমানুষ দাড়িয়ে আমায় উদ্দেশ্য করে হস্থমৈথুন করছে,তার প্রতিবাদ করতে আমি দৌড়ে তাকে ধরতে গিয়ে ব্যর্থ হলাম,আমার বাবাও আমার পিছে দৌড়ে এসেছে।লোকে আমার দৌড়ে আসা দেখে বলল,"তুমি তো জোয়ান মেয়ে মানুষ,তোমার কি শোভা পায় অমন পুরুষ লোকের পিছনে দৌড়ানো?"আমি অবাক বনে গেলাম!বাবা জিজ্ঞেস করছিল কি হয়েছে,কিন্তু আমি কেমন করে তাকে বলি,বাবা তোমার বয়সী একজন লোক আমায় উদ্দেশ্য করে এমন ঘৃণ্য কাজ করেছে! সবার কত অভিযোগ মেয়ে মানুষ রাতে বের হয়ো না,ওভাবে হেঁটো না!মেয়ে মানুষ একটু জোরে পা ফেললেও না কি মাটি গোসা করে!মেয়ে মানুষ হয়ে কেন তোমার পোশাক আষ্টেপৃষ্ঠে জড়িয়ে রাখো নি?আচ্ছা,যারা এ কথা গুলো বলে,তারা কি কখনো ভেবে দেখেছে,আট মাস বয়সী একটা শিশু যদি ধর্ষনের স্বীকার হতে পারে,তবে আমরা আষ্টেপৃষ্ঠে কাপড় কেন লোহা দিয়ে নিজেকে আড়াল করলেও ঐ অমানুষ গুলো থেকে নিরাপদে নেই।আর কতই বা চুপ থাকবো?চলো এইবারে আওয়াজ তুলি,আরও একবার গর্জে উঠে জানিয়ে দেই এ পৃথিবীকে—আমরা নারী হওয়ার আগে একজন মানুষ,কোনো ভোগের বস্তু নই।আরও একবার ওই নরপিশাচদের কে মনে করিয়ে দেই তাদের মতন অজাত দের ভ্রুন আমরা চাইলেই ধ্বংস করে দিতে পারি।আজ যে পৃথিবীতে আমাদের নিরাপত্তা নেই,সে পৃথিবীতে একজন নারী হিসেবে আমিও আমার ভবিষ্যতে হতে যাওয়া ছেলের ভ্রুন নষ্ট করতে দ্বিধান্বিত হবো না,হলাম নাহয় আমি এক পাপী মা,কিন্তু আমি মা হয়ে তো দেখতে পারবো না আমার ছেলে ভবিষ্যতে কোনো মেয়ের জীবন নষ্টের কারন হয়ে দাঁড়াবে!অমন পরিস্থিতির সম্মুখীন না হতে আমি নাহয় ছেলে সন্তানের মা হবই না৷কিন্তু এ পৃথিবী থেকে এসব অমানুষদের কে তারিয়েই আমি ক্ষান্ত হবো।

#share_ur_ones

#parishaeashablog

কিছুদিন আগের এক ঘটনা-আমি আমার বাবা'র সাথে ঢাকা মেডিকেলে এক কাজে গিয়েছি,বাবা একজন পরিচিত ডাক্তার এর সাথে কথা বলছিল,আমি ওয়েটিং রুমে বসে,হঠাৎ দেখি পর্দার ধারে একজন অমানুষ দাড়িয়ে আমায় উদ্দেশ্য করে হস্থমৈথুন করছে,তার প্রতিবাদ করতে আমি দৌড়ে তাকে ধরতে গিয়ে ব্যর্থ হলাম,আমার বাবাও আমার পিছে দৌড়ে এসেছে।লোকে আমার দৌড়ে আসা দেখে বলল,"তুমি তো জোয়ান মেয়ে মানুষ,তোমার কি শোভা পায় অমন পুরুষ লোকের পিছনে দৌড়ানো?"আমি অবাক বনে গেলাম!বাবা জিজ্ঞেস করছিল কি হয়েছে,কিন্তু আমি কেমন করে তাকে বলি,বাবা তোমার বয়সী একজন লোক আমায় উদ্দেশ্য করে এমন ঘৃণ্য কাজ করেছে! সবার কত অভিযোগ মেয়ে মানুষ রাতে বের হয়ো না,ওভাবে হেঁটো না!মেয়ে মানুষ একটু জোরে পা ফেললেও না কি মাটি গোসা করে!মেয়ে মানুষ হয়ে কেন তোমার পোশাক আষ্টেপৃষ্ঠে জড়িয়ে রাখো নি?আচ্ছা,যারা এ কথা গুলো বলে,তারা কি কখনো ভেবে দেখেছে,আট মাস বয়সী একটা শিশু যদি ধর্ষনের স্বীকার হতে পারে,তবে আমরা আষ্টেপৃষ্ঠে কাপড় কেন লোহা দিয়ে নিজেকে আড়াল করলেও ঐ অমানুষ গুলো থেকে নিরাপদে নেই।আর কতই বা চুপ থাকবো?চলো এইবারে আওয়াজ তুলি,আরও একবার গর্জে উঠে জানিয়ে দেই এ পৃথিবীকে—আমরা নারী হওয়ার আগে একজন মানুষ,কোনো ভোগের বস্তু নই।আরও একবার ওই নরপিশাচদের কে মনে করিয়ে দেই তাদের মতন অজাত দের ভ্রুন আমরা চাইলেই ধ্বংস করে দিতে পারি।আজ যে পৃথিবীতে আমাদের নিরাপত্তা নেই,সে পৃথিবীতে একজন নারী হিসেবে আমিও আমার ভবিষ্যতে হতে যাওয়া ছেলের ভ্রুন নষ্ট করতে দ্বিধান্বিত হবো না,হলাম নাহয় আমি এক পাপী মা,কিন্তু আমি মা হয়ে তো দেখতে পারবো না আমার ছেলে ভবিষ্যতে কোনো মেয়ের জীবন নষ্টের কারন হয়ে দাঁড়াবে!অমন পরিস্থিতির সম্মুখীন না হতে আমি নাহয় ছেলে সন্তানের মা হবই না৷কিন্তু এ পৃথিবী থেকে এসব অমানুষদের কে তারিয়েই আমি ক্ষান্ত হবো।

stop_filter_tweet: কিছু দিন ধরে খুব আতংকে আছি , একজন আমাকে বেশ বিরক্ত করতো বিভিন্ন ভাবে , সেদিন হঠাৎ ডাইনিং'র বেসিনে মুখ ধোবার সময় দেখলাম সে পাশের বাসার ছাদ থেকে আমায় দেখতে উঁকি দিচ্ছে ! প্রতিবাদ করতে আওয়াজ তুলতে চেয়েছিলাম , কিন্তু পারি নাই ! আমার মন বলল , '' না , এখন আওয়াজ তুলো না , তুমি এখন রাস্তায় একলা চলো , যদি তোমার মুখখানা মানুষরূপী এই বখাটে ঝলসে দেয় ? যদি সে তোমার স্বত্তাকে কেড়ে নেয় ? `` আমার আমি আমায় থামিয়ে দিলো , কিন্তু আমি জানি , এই অত্যাচার এখানেই শেষ হয়ে যাবে না , এমন অমানুষ আমার আশেপাশে প্রতিনিয়ত ঘুড়ে বেড়াবে।কেমন করে সেই অমানুষদের সাথে আমি পারবো ? আমি তো এখন রাস্তায় একলা চলি ! কিছুদিন আগের এক ঘটনা-আমি আমার বাবা'র সাথে ঢাকা মেডিকেলে এক কাজে গিয়েছি , বাবা একজন পরিচিত ডাক্তার এর সাথে কথা বলছিল , আমি ওয়েটিং রুমে বসে , হঠাৎ দেখি পর্দার ধারে একজন অমানুষ দাড়িয়ে আমায় উদ্দেশ্য করে হস্থমৈথুন করছে , তার প্রতিবাদ করতে আমি দৌড়ে তাকে ধরতে গিয়ে ব্যর্থ হলাম , আমার বাবাও আমার পিছে দৌড়ে এসেছে।লোকে আমার দৌড়ে আসা দেখে বলল , '' তুমি তো জোয়ান মেয়ে মানুষ , তোমার কি শোভা পায় অমন পুরুষ লোকের পিছনে দৌড়ানো ? `` আমি অবাক বনে গেলাম ! বাবা জিজ্ঞেস করছিল কি হয়েছে , কিন্তু আমি কেমন করে তাকে বলি , বাবা তোমার বয়সী একজন লোক আমায় উদ্দেশ্য করে এমন ঘৃণ্য কাজ করেছে ! সবার কত অভিযোগ মেয়ে মানুষ রাতে বের হয়ো না , ওভাবে হেঁটো না ! মেয়ে মানুষ একটু জোরে পা ফেললেও না কি মাটি গোসা করে ! মেয়ে মানুষ হয়ে কেন তোমার পোশাক আষ্টেপৃষ্ঠে জড়িয়ে রাখো নি ? আচ্ছা , যারা এ কথা গুলো বলে , তারা কি কখনো ভেবে দেখেছে , আট মাস বয়সী একটা শিশু যদি ধর্ষনের স্বীকার হতে পারে , তবে আমরা আষ্টেপৃষ্ঠে কাপড় কেন লোহা দিয়ে নিজেকে আড়াল করলেও ঐ অমানুষ গুলো থেকে নিরাপদে নেই।আর কতই বা চুপ থাকবো ? চলো এইবারে আওয়াজ তুলি , আরও একবার গর্জে উঠে জানিয়ে দেই এ পৃথিবীকে—আমরা নারী হওয়ার আগে একজন মানুষ , কোনো ভোগের বস্তু নই।আরও একবার ওই নরপিশাচদের কে মনে করিয়ে দেই তাদের মতন অজাত দের ভ্রুন আমরা চাইলেই ধ্বংস করে দিতে পারি।আজ যে পৃথিবীতে আমাদের নিরাপত্তা নেই , সে পৃথিবীতে একজন নারী হিসেবে আমিও আমার ভবিষ্যতে হতে যাওয়া ছেলের ভ্রুন নষ্ট করতে দ্বিধান্বিত হবো না , হলাম নাহয় আমি এক পাপী মা , কিন্তু আমি মা হয়ে তো দেখতে পারবো না আমার ছেলে ভবিষ্যতে কোনো মেয়ের জীবন নষ্টের কারন হয়ে দাঁড়াবে ! অমন পরিস্থিতির সম্মুখীন না হতে আমি নাহয় ছেলে সন্তানের মা হবই না৷কিন্তু এ পৃথিবী থেকে এসব অমানুষদের কে তারিয়েই আমি ক্ষান্ত হবো। aise_ur_voice_against_sexuall_harresment hare_ur_ones ot_ashamed_of_urself roud_being_a_women

চলো এইবারে আওয়াজ তুলি , আরও একবার গর্জে উঠে জানিয়ে দেই এ পৃথিবীকে—আমরা নারী হওয়ার আগে একজন মানুষ , কোনো ভোগের বস্তু নই।আরও একবার ওই নরপিশাচদের কে মনে করিয়ে দেই তাদের মতন অজাত দের ভ্রুন আমরা চাইলেই ধ্বংস করে দিতে পারি।আজ যে পৃথিবীতে আমাদের নিরাপত্তা নেই , সে পৃথিবীতে একজন নারী হিসেবে আমিও আমার ভবিষ্যতে হতে যাওয়া ছেলের ভ্রুন নষ্ট করতে দ্বিধান্বিত হবো না , হলাম নাহয় আমি এক পাপী মা , কিন্তু আমি মা হয়ে তো দেখতে পারবো না আমার ছেলে ভবিষ্যতে কোনো মেয়ের জীবন নষ্টের কারন হয়ে দাঁড়াবে ! অমন পরিস্থিতির সম্মুখীন না হতে আমি নাহয় ছেলে সন্তানের মা হবই না৷কিন্তু এ পৃথিবী থেকে এসব অমানুষদের কে তারিয়েই আমি ক্ষান্ত হবো। aise_ur_voice_against_sexuall_harres hare_ur_on ot_ashamed_of_urself roud_being_a_women

text:
buzz it or bash it? first and foremost, ain’t nobody here for #violadavis revelation where others have prophesied. #dryerbuzz 
only took seven years to come back here, following #thehelp where davis played a maid and launched an indictment on black and female audiences for wanting more. “that very mindset, that a lot of african americans have, is destroying the black artist,” she said once in an interview about her then movie with its oscar buzz.

but now we’re — her revelation, hollywood having come no closer to change. #metoo movie having set casting couches a fire. earning potential still hovering with the lowest of the lows. reorientation on screen still an issues. 
few willing to follow the success of the recent billion dollar blockbuster which appealed to black women #blackpanther.

we said it then and will say it again. let’s put it in the words of my be of viola’s most beloved roles from #fences... but we held on to you, viola. we took all our feelings, our wants and needs, our dreams...and we buried them inside you. we planted ourselves inside you and waited to bloom. and it didn't take me us seven years to find out the soil was hard and rocky and it wasn't never gonna bloom.

text:
*warning // talk of sexual violence* 
i was 13. how can a 13 year old consent? my boyfriend at the time was demanding and manipulative. if i said no he would tell people i had anyway. he bullied me into doing what he wanted, told me if i didn’t do certain things i didn’t care about him, if i left him he threatened to kill himself. 
this was normalised by his constant and frequent consumption of pornography. i don’t believe he knew what he was doing and i believe he still has no clue now. this behaviour was and still is normalised and swept under the carpet by our society, i mean boys will be boys right? 
it took me years to get away, i thought it was normal. i didn’t realise until i was 19 that this was so wrong and i had been over sexualised from such a young age. speaking to others i realised how many people have had similar experiences. 
a 13 year old cannot consent and should not be pressured and manipulated into performing sexual acts. 
if i had known what consent was from an early age this could have been prevented. instead, he took away my innocence. i will never get those years back to be a young teenager. i am so angry because something as simple as education about consent could have saved me from years of feeling isolated, depressed and confused. 
it’s time to speak out and educate. 
#letstalkconsent #metoo #timesup #iwillnotbesilenced #speakout #endrapeculture #thisisnotconsent #believesurvivors #enoughisenough #assaultsupport #sexualassaultawareness #speakoutweek
name: #metoo Support Society GS

if i had known what consent was from an early age this could have been prevented. instead, he took away my innocence. i will never get those years back to be a young teenager. i am so angry because something as simple as education about consent could have saved me from years of feeling isolated, depressed and confused. 
it’s time to speak out and educate.

text:
today, for the #16days of activism against gender-based violence campaign, we’re highlighting the activism of amina, a muslim womens’ organisation based in dundee, uk. the organisation works to ‘empower, inspire and support muslim women’ and is ‘committed to raising awareness of the needs of muslim and bme women who have experienced violence.’
.
amina has produced ‘hopscotch’, a film by roxana vilk. the film explores street harassment experienced by muslim women and women of colour and is based on a real life incident. speaking of the idea behind its production, amina said “…the harassment women experience on the street forms part of their experience of racism, of islamophobia, and of men’s violence against women…. street harassment is one of the most pervasive forms of gender-based violence, and yet least legislated against…further, research published by anti-islamophobia charity, tell mama uk, discovered that of the 300% increase in islamophobic hate crimes in 2015, the majority of incidents were targeted at muslim women, by white men, in public places.”
.
“street harassment forms part of a continuum of violence against women; with sexist and misogynistic language at one end of the spectrum, and the rape and murder of women at the other…when we dismiss or normalise the violence that women experience, we further embed that message and contribute to the inequality and diminished sense of freedom which women, muslim women and women of colour face when moving through public spaces.  this is why films like hopscotch, need to be seen and discussed.” -amina
.

text:
this homemade creamy jain vegan pasta ❤️💛.
*recipe* for 130gm pasta :
*ingredients*:
• 130 gm pasta • 5 tomatoes •1 green chilli
• 8 cashews
• capsicum (all three colors if possible)
• lemon
*spices /masala*
• 1tsp  bishop's weed -
•1tsp oregano and chilli flakes  each
•1/4 tsp turmeric
•1/2 tsp red pepper
•1tsp black pepper •1/2 tsp jeeravan
•salt as per taste •3 tbsp olive oil *method*
-cook the pasta (i did in pressure cooker for quick results)
- make puree of 3 tomaotes and green chilli and keep it besides - take cashews and a little water to grind them in a jar until a creamy mixture thicker than cream
-take a pan and heat it on high flame for around 2 minutes - add red pepper,garam masala , jeeravan, turmeric into the pan and cook for 1 minute
-now keep the mix aside
-take olive oil in the pan heat it a little and add bishop's seed into it
- stir a while and add chopped capsicum into it
- after 2 minutes add tomatoes and stir them fir 2 minutes
-now add tomato puree and add the masala mix - now keep stirring until the color of puree darkens (for 2-3 minutes)
-now add the cashew cream and again stir for 1 minute ( you can add basil leaves also)
- now add salt and half black pepper to the mix
- now add the pasta -add remaining black pepper , salt ,oregano and chilli flakes - mix for 30 sec and stir -season with basil leaves ,chilli flakes and oregano and serve .
.

-take a pan and heat it on high flame for around 2 minutes - add red pepper,garam masala , jeeravan, turmeric into the pan and cook for 1 minute
-now keep the mix aside
-take olive oil in the pan heat it a little and add bishop's seed into it
- stir a while and add chopped capsicum into it
- after 2 minutes add tomatoes and stir them fir 2 minutes
-now add tomato puree and add the masala mix - now keep stirring until the color of puree darkens (for 2-3 minutes)
-now add the cashew cream and again stir for 1 minute ( you can add basil leaves also)
- now add salt and half black pepper to the mix
- now add the pasta -add remaining black pepper , salt ,oregano and chilli flakes - mix for 30 sec and stir -season with basil leaves ,chilli flakes and oregano and serve .

text:
today we will talk about lena dunham’s apology (a word i’m applying extremely loosely) and then, i hope, we will return to the proper amount of talking about lena dunham, which is never.

a year ago, dunham lied in order to discredit a woman who had just gone to the police to report a sexual assault.

on wednesday, she penned a rambling, pretentious opus about women in hollywood (“heroines have emerged. we are cracking open windows and beating down doors. the air is circulating and the light is pouring in,”) and snuck a whiny, half-hearted mea culpa into the ninth paragraph.

we’re so used to dunham apologizing at this point (lena dunham apologizes is an actual twitter handle) that we went ahead and lumped this garbage onto her giant apology pile.

but before we toss them aside, her words are worth examining, if only as a reminder that when we screw up, which all of us do, we should apologize directly, authentically and humbly.

dunham did nothing of the sort.

first, let’s back up: last november, actress aurora perrineau filed a police report accusing “girls” writer and executive producer murray miller of raping her in 2012, when she was 17 years old. (“girls” was dunham’s hbo show.) miller said perrineau was making the whole thing up and accused her of trying to extract money from him.

dunham sent a statement to the hollywood reporter, co-written with “girls” showrunner jenni konner, saying, “while our first instinct is to listen to every woman’s story, our insider knowledge of murray’s situation makes us confident that sadly this accusation is one of the 3 percent of assault cases that are misreported every year. ... it is a true shame to add to that number, as outside of hollywood women still struggle to be believed. we stand by murray and this is all we’ll be saying about this issue.” until wednesday, when she admitted the “insider knowledge” thing was a bunch of baloney. “and so i made a terrible mistake,” dunham wrote in wednesday’s piece, after talking about harvey weinstein, wage equality, systemic bias, “layers of crinoline and repressed rage,” an op-ed she wrote last year and disguising her own pain with medication and chronic overwork. #metoo

text:
чтоб не обвинили в харассменте⠀
⠀
в последние пару лет эта тема вызывает немало обсуждений. ⠀
⠀
и вот журналисты bloomberg спросили у финансистов с уолл-стрит, как они общаются со женщинами-коллегами.⠀
⠀ ▪️получился примерно такой свод правил: ⠀
⠀
- приглашать на бизнес-ланч женщин только старше 35;⠀
⠀
- сидеть в баре с женщинами после работы тоже не стоит;⠀
⠀
- не сидеть рядом с женщинами в самолете;⠀
⠀
- во время командировок жить только на разных этажах гостиницы;⠀
⠀
- обсуждать деловые вопросы в присутствии третьих лиц;⠀
⠀
- ни в коем случае не оставаться один на один.⠀
⠀
нашлись, конечно, и те, кто озвучил адекватное правило: «просто не быть козлом». но, видимо, для некоторых это слишком сложно. кто-то даже прямо сказал, что боится потерять контроль во время общения с женщиной тет-а-тет.⠀
⠀
▪️что не так с этими правилами?⠀
⠀
- авторы bloomberg пришли к выводу (и я с этим согласна), что это создаёт масштабную половую сегрегации в бизнесе сша. получается, что, например, с начальником-мужчиной больше общаться и лучше налаживать контакт может только сотрудник-мужчина. ⠀
⠀
- эти «принципы» не защищают женщин. зато мужчинам, которые не готовы относиться к своим коллегам обоих полов одинаково, дарят спокойствие. ⠀
⠀
- и такие правила бесполезны. если человек козёл, то его ничто не остановит.⠀
⠀
- это создаёт только видимость равенства и равноправия. на деле же от женщин финансисты чураются. это при том, что не всех мужчин привлекают женщины, а не всех женщин – мужчины. ⠀
⠀
такой вот перевёртыш. условия изменились: открыто вести себя, как козёл, получится не всегда. но саму козлиность кто-то предпочитает сохранить в себе.⠀
⠀
💬 а что вы думаете по поводу сложившейся ситуации?⠀
⠀
#полозок #полозокразмышляет ⠀
⠀

text:
on december 6, 1989, a man entered a classroom of the prestigious montréal engineering school, l’école polytechnique. with a gun in his arms, he  asked the men to leave. once he had separated the female students from their male peers, he told the women they didn’t belong there and that he would kill them for being feminists. then, he shot them. he continued, classroom by classroom, before taking his own life.
.
this man’s application to the same school had been rejected, twice. male entitlement, his impetus for murdering 14 brilliant women.
.
still today, we continue to see the toxic impact of male entitlement on women’s lives. . 
entitlement to our attention, 
our compliance, 
our bodies, 
and our love.
.
women and girls continue to be sexually harassed in our streets, schools, and work places. the men we already know are the most likely to sexually assault us. our homes are where we are most at risk of being murdered. 
women are still dying because we won’t fall in line.
...
today, take a moment to remember the women whose lives were lost at l’école polytechnique. 
then, take a moment for all of the women whose lives have been lost for simply being women. 
the women who took up space. 
the women who said no. 
the women who loved violent men.
.
this is more than a day of remembrance. this day is a call to action. so, i hope you’ll also take a moment to consider what you can do to change this reality. often, this can be as simple as being willing to speak up. 💜
.
#metoo #endvaw #december6 #16days #canfem #hearmetoo #vaw #jemesouviens

entitlement to our attention, 
our compliance, 
our bodies, 
and our love.
.
women and girls continue to be sexually harassed in our streets, schools, and work places. the men we already know are the most likely to sexually assault us. our homes are where we are most at risk of being murdered. 
women are still dying because we won’t fall in line.
...
today, take a moment to remember the women whose lives were lost at l’école polytechnique. 
then, take a moment for all of the women whose lives have been lost for simply being women. 
the women who took up space. 
the women who said no. 
the women who loved violent men.
.
this is more than a day of remembrance. this day is a call to action. so, i hope you’ll also take a moment to consider what you can do to change this reality. often, this can be as simple as being willing to speak up. 💜

text:

.

text:
2018 miss universe #spain pageant contestant, angela ponce, a #biological xy male who has undergone #gender #reassignment #surgery and #hormone therapy, has not only become the first trans contestant in the miss universe competition, but the odds makers' hands-down favorite to win it all.

basically, if you're a biological xx, you ought not to compete (sarc.!). whether it's #soccer, #wrestling, #pageantry, #modeling, #athletics, xy are always going to be better (denser) in most #muscle, etc circumstances. it's simply #biology.

gotta love the world of the 'progressive' far far
left.. if you're cis-xx, roll over.. at least that's what they're saying in the #fashion/#modeling/#cycling/#track/#hottie etc. dept. as we just saw with the #missbumbum2018 #competition in #brazil. and basically everywhere. #everywhere.

saying this as someone who was on the bod of the miss #universe thingie last yr. never met as many xx who hated other xx as much as some of the #contestants did.. hyper-competitive. sick. sad. not surprising.

wonder why cis xy guys don't even bother to talk with '#western' 'women'? this is why. oh, and the '#metoo' thingie.

what i'm saying is not #politically correct. but it's #biologically and #biochemically accurate.

this is 2018 #feminism.
xx cis-'females' need not apply.

xy make better xx (sarc.!)

text:
why wear dresses?

text:
last night i went to the cinema. as i was walking to the bus stop, i saw a man walking to the same direction. i looked at my phone trying to confirm the bus schedule. as i was waiting to cross the road, the man caught up and said hi. i turned around, perplexed because i was so focused on my phone and bus schedule, so i didn't immediately respond. he must have seen my confused look and thought that i might be scared, so he said with a smile, 'i said hi because i didn't want to scare you.' and i responded, 'that's fine, thank you 😊.' well, actually i wasn't scared at all. true that naturally i'll feel scared and a little bit paranoid when walking alone at night. but when i first saw him, i knew that, from his attire, he was one of the construction workers near my apt, and somehow i felt safe. but i think i need to share this story to appreciate his kindness. he knew that the presence of an unknown man can be scary for women, especially with the #metoo movement, so maybe he's trying to put me at ease or make me feel safe. i myself am often too dense when thinking about such things, because i often think that i'm just being paranoid so most of the times i am convinced that, well, nobody will harm me, i am safe. but when someone goes to the extent thinking and understanding that we might feel scared and does something about it, i think it should be appreciated. so we crossed the road. i went to the left to where the bus stop was, he went to the right as the lights replaced the darkness of the night.
.
.
.
.
.
.
.
📷 s8.
.
july 30, 2018.
.

text:
ocean's 8 (gary ross), 2018
laufzeit: 1h 50min
bewertung: 6/10
debbie ocean ist die schwester von danny ocean und steht ihm in nichts nach. die meiste zeit hatte sie im gefängnis mit der planung ihres nächsten coups verbracht. hierzu hat sie auch ihre eigene crew, denn es geht um eine halskette aus diamanten im wert von 150 mio $.
als filmfan wird man einfach nicht das gefühl los, dass in hollywood die ideen ausgehen. so wird einfach etwas erfolgreiches aus der vergangenheit genommen und neu aufgewärmt. in diesem fall wird dies noch mit frauen besetzt. ist dies eine folge der #metoo bewegung? hier geht es aber aus meiner sicht in die hose. man hat hier nichts neues geschaffen, gar nicht die mühe gemacht einen neuen touch einzubringen. es wäre viel sinnvoller gewesen einen eigenständigen film zu machen und nicht einen abklatsch! selbst die rollen sind 1:1 übernommen worden. 
um es klarzustellen: der film ist solide, aber bietet nichts neues im vergleich zu der ocean's trilogie. außer die weiblichen darsteller.
anne hathaway ist wieder mal wundervoll, ich mag ihre wirklich sympathische art. insgesamt bietet der film solide unterhaltung nach dem motto "kann man gucken, muss man aber nicht".

text:
west palm beach, fla. -- a last-minute settlement was reached tuesday in a long-running florida lawsuit involving a politically connected financier accused of sexually abusing dozens of teenage girls, clearing the way for the victims' lawyers to try to unravel a once-secret agreement that prevented federal criminal prosecution of the financier.

the non-prosecution agreement protecting jeffrey epstein was negotiated a decade ago by prosecutors in the south florida u.s. attorney's office, which was then run by current labor secretary alexander acosta. it is the subject of a separate federal lawsuit in florida filed by victims who say the deal trampled their rights to be heard. "that injustice needs to be addressed and will be addressed," said attorney jack scarola, who represents fellow lawyer bradley edwards in the lawsuit settled tuesday. "there is no justification for the broad scope of immunity that was granted." epstein, 65, pleaded guilty in 2008 to two state charges after reaching the non-prosecution deal with acosta's office while under investigation for sexually abusing dozens of teenage girls. he served 13 months in jail, was required to reach financial settlements with many of the victims and registered as a convicted sex offender.

but epstein could have faced a possible life sentence if federal prosecutors had pursued a draft 57-page indictment that was never filed. now, scarola and edwards say that possibility still exists, and the victims - some of whom were only 13 or 14 when they were molested - may yet get their day in federal court amid a national #metoo movement that seeks to hold sexual harassers and abusers to account. "they're willing to talk. they want to share their stories," edwards said.

text:
an open letter :

dear society,

it takes a lot of courage to speak up. there are times when we do not know what to do. there are several mind battles going on ( what my parents will think? or what my friends will think? or how will i face everyone? and what not). even after going through so much, we further have to bear the mental torture of these never ending questions. speak up at that time, is what you suggest. but how do i, when so many taboos surround and blur my vision. and who will support me. no evidence, then nothing.

but then it's never too late, as they say. #metoo gave me the strength to speak up. encouraged me to open those pages of my life which i had buried years ago.

this is when i need your support, not your judgement. it was hard for me to share, but now i did. i was not strong back then, but now i am.

also its my humble request to all people out there, do not misuse this cause for taking revenge or any other benefits. 
one fake incident and everyone will get a reason to pinpoint at this campaign. 
and also a word for all the memes and joke pages - dear people your business is to make people happy, but while doing that don't forget that not everything in this world is a joke. do your job, but not by making joke of the campaign which has given encouragement to many of us.

and shoutout to all the courageous people out there. remember its okay to speak! and never too late to speak!! yours,
someone helped by #metoo

we stand with survivors, we believe you.

今日はイシダイ〜🐟！ このカッコイイ名前！はっきりした縞模様！
…からは想像できぬクリクリの目👀とツルッとしたお口💋！イルカ🐬の顔をギュっと集めたようなお顔をしていませんか😚？笑
（誰かわかってくださーい😫笑）

さてさて、この綺麗な縞模様には、秘密がありましたよ〜(´⊙ω⊙`)💡 幼魚、若魚にははっきりとした黒色の縞があり、メスは成長してもこの縞が残りますが、オスは成長するにしたがって縞が消えてしまい、やがて黒めの銀色一色になるんだそうな🧐！ なるほど…💡
この子は、イシダイ♀ということですね😏✨ 今が旬のイシダイ🐟！皆さんもスーパーで見かけた際は、オスメス当てをしてみてくださいね🐟💓笑

text:
shreya arora is using her art to explore consent in india 🇮🇳 she has created a paper dress made from printed tweets from india's #metoo movement. shreya says, “i hope every single sexual harasser watches this movement keenly, and is aware of the global community it has created.” 🌎 she thinks that before we can learn what consent is, “we need to unlearn the things we assume are consent. victim blaming often teaches us to assume that if a woman was out alone at night, or wearing something provocative, or had a lot to drink, she was somehow asking for it. to talk about how it is never the victim's fault, i wanted to create a museum of nonconsent - a space that documents these things symbolically.”
____
the dress is handmade using origami, and features accounts from sexual assault survivors with their consent. shreya says that while the dress style is something some people “would deem 'provocative', it is a statement on the fact that no matter what a victim wore, it is never their fault. i hope #metoo creates a sisterhood where no woman has to be victim blamed again.”
____
photographers: saurabh srivastava, abhishek kumar nirala, shreya arora
model: supreetha krishnan #india #women #100women #consent #metoo #dress #art

text:
sakshi mallik is the first indian woman wrestler to bag an olympic medal. 
as a young wrestler, sakshi faced a lot of criticism in her village. as wrestling was not considered to be a 'women' sport. nonetheless, she continued her intensive training, juggling it with her academics & later with an indian railways job.

it was her medal at the olympics, that brought her victory against all the pre-conceived notions and stubborn mindsets. 
sanfe salutes sakshi's motivation and grit to achieve her vision. you have inspired many women to #standupforyourself

text:
today is international day of remembrance and action on violence against women. it is the day of launching montaha hidefi's very difficult to read, 'raw and authentic' memoir. it is a day to reiterate and say loudly #enoughisenough.
in an interview with @ocpubhfx montaha shared this message for other survivors of abuse: "it’s hard for someone who lived for a long time, hiding the shame the abuse has inflicted them with, to open up and disclose the events and emotions that they tried to bury for such a long time. this is because of fear of being stigmatizing by society. we fear that people will not believe us, or if they did believe us, we fear that they will say that we have brought this upon ourselves. and we also fear the ridicule of a society that would say, 'if that were true, why did you wait so long to disclose this? why didn’t you speak up and denounce the abuser then and there?' we have seen this happening, not to mention that abusers would usually deny their wrong doing. so there are many factors that prevent people like me from coming forward and speaking about their stories of abuse. however, while writing about my experiences, i found that the process of remembering the events, although painful, was also therapeutic. i found consolation in relieving myself of the secret. although i know there might be consequences, i feel that the time is right now to speak up as more people are ready to listen and believe the abused. this wouldn’t have happened if it wasn’t for the #metoo movement and what unfolded after it. so, speak up and don’t fear the ridicule or consequences."
.
.
#metoo #survivor #bookstagram #bookrelease #bookshelf #book #timesup #womenempowerment #nomore #bookclub #bookstagrammer #nomoreabuse #stoptheabuse

today is international day of remembrance and action on violence against women. it is the day of launching montaha hidefi's very difficult to read, 'raw and authentic' memoir. it is a day to reiterate and say loudly #enoughisenough.
in an interview with @ocpubhfx montaha shared this message for other survivors of abuse: "it’s hard for someone who lived for a long time, hiding the shame the abuse has inflicted them with, to open up and disclose the events and emotions that they tried to bury for such a long time. this is because of fear of being stigmatizing by society. we fear that people will not believe us, or if they did believe us, we fear that they will say that we have brought this upon ourselves. and we also fear the ridicule of a society that would say, 'if that were true, why did you wait so long to disclose this? why didn’t you speak up and denounce the abuser then and there?' we have seen this happening, not to mention that abusers would usually deny their wrong doing. so there are many factors that prevent people like me from coming forward and speaking about their stories of abuse. however, while writing about my experiences, i found that the process of remembering the events, although painful, was also therapeutic. i found consolation in relieving myself of the secret. although i know there might be consequences, i feel that the time is right now to speak up as more people are ready to listen and believe the abused. this wouldn’t have happened if it wasn’t for the #metoo movement and what unfolded after it. so, speak up and don’t fear the ridicule or consequences."
.
.
